title: world's best brownies
directions: Melt
oleo and chocolate together.
Cool slightly.
Mix flour and
sugar	together;
add	to
chocolate mixture.	Add unbeaten eggs
and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Line two 8 x 8-inch pans with heavy duty aluminum foil and brush thoroughly with melted oleo.
Pour
brownie mix in pans and bake at 375° for 30
minutes. Cool.
May
be
frosted
with
frosting mix, dusted with powdered
sugar or left plain.
Cut into squares. Makes 50. Freezes well.

title: master mix (cookies)
directions: Stir baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar into measured flour (sift 3 times).
Cut in the shortening; work in with fingers until mix is the consistency of cornmeal.
Store in covered container in cool place.
Will keep six weeks without refrigeration.

title: whipping cream biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix flour and cream until dough leaves side of bowl and rounds up into ball.
Sprinkle dough with flour and knead 10 times.
Roll or pat dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured 2-inch round cutter.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: marinated vegetables(this can be served either as a salad or as an appetizer.)
directions: Prepare vegetables and place in a large bowl.
Mix marinade ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill at least 12 hours.
Drain 1 hour before serving.
Serves approximately 8.

title: rice pilaff
directions: Brown butter, onion, celery and rice.
Stir in Lipton chicken noodle soup, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Remove and let stand 10 minutes with cover on.

title: refrigerator pickle
directions: Mix well; let set for 20 minutes.
Pack in jars and refrigerate.

title: lite fruit salad dressing
directions: Fold together mayonnaise and Cool Whip.
Stir in fruit juice to make consistency desired.
Good on fresh fruit or jello salad. Keeps several days in the refrigerator.

title: cheesecake fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme, mixing well.
Add 1 tablespoon grated orange rind and dash of ground ginger.
Stir well; serve with fresh fruit.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In medium bowl, shred half bowl of lettuce.
Mix together celery, onion and sweet pepper.
Spread layer over lettuce, then spread English peas.
Whip enough mayonnaise to make layer 1/4-inch thick; sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle on bacon bits.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: mandarin orange and pineapple cake
directions: Mix together with beater.
Grease and flour 3 layer pans. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: flannel cakes
directions: Combine flour with cream; beat in eggs until smooth.
Add baking powder to milk, then slowly add to flour mixture, beating well.
Fry with a little lard added to griddle before each cake.

title: bubble stuff
directions: Mix Joy and water in bowl or jar.
Add syrup. Mix well or shake.
Put in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil water, rice, raisins and salt.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Add nutmeg.
When rice has cooled, add to pudding and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: stir-fried broccoli and carrots
directions: Mix cornstarch and water in bowl.
Heat oil in wok or 12-inch skillet.
Add broccoli, carrots and onion; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add chicken broth and salt; cover and cook 3 minutes.
Stir cornstarch mixture in vegetables.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add water chestnuts, mushrooms and oyster sauce.
Cook and stir 30 seconds.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, egg yolks and sugar well.
Add lemon extract. Mix pecans and fruit with 2 cups sifted flour in a large pan. Blend in the remaining 3 cups flour to butter and sugar mixture. Mix soda and warm water.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well and add fruit and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to other ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured Bundt or angel cake pans.
Bake in a 250° oven for 3 hours.
Place a pan of water under cake while baking to prevent burning.

title: appetizers
directions: Mix and spread on rye bread.
Sprinkle bacon over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: dilly beans(canning recipe)
directions: Trim beans and remove strings.
Combine salt, vinegar and water.
Bring to boil.
Add seasonings to each clean hot jar.
Pack beans in jars; cover with boiling liquid, leaving 1/2-inch head space; seal (beans must be completely covered by liquid).

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add sugar and Kool-Aid.
Mix well.
Add cold water; pour into popsicle containers and freeze.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl (except peaches, cream cheese and sugar).
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared 9 or 10-inch pie pan with greased bottom and sides. Place peaches (reserving juice) onto batter.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and 3 tablespoons reserved peach juice.
Mix for 2 minutes in a bowl.
Spoon within 1-inch of edges.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Filling will appear soft. Store in refrigerator.

title: basic fruit leather(method:  pot)
directions: Place fruit in blender and liquefy.
Add sugar.
Boil mixture. Spoon thinly and evenly on pieces of plastic wrap.
Let dry for several days, in sun or on table under several lamps.
It is done when it can be peeled from plastic wrap.
Roll it up in the plastic.

title: parfait pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add ice cream by spoonful. Chill 15 minutes, then add berries.
Pour into crust and chill at least one hour.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Blend cheese and butter, stir in flour, mustard, pepper and sherry.
Roll one teaspoon of cheese mixture around each olive, covering completely.
When ready to serve, place on a cookie sheet and bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: turkey steak
directions: Parboil a turkey of 25 to 26 pounds until fairly done.
Lift out breast and cut steaks as from a beef tenderloin.
Dip steaks in a batter made of milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour, then dunk back into batter and finish off with bread crumbs.
Fry in fat (350°) until golden brown.
Serve with onion rings made in the same way.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut the broccoli, cauliflower, raisins and bacon into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients; let set a short time.
Serves 8.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add shrimp and vegetables; mix thoroughly. Heat oil in skillet.
Place about 1/4 cup egg mixture in oil; brown lightly on each side.
Serve with sweet-sour sauce and soy sauce and sprinkle with green onions.

title: hot lemon pudding
directions: Combine flour, butter and 3/4 cup sugar with beaten egg yolks. Add lemon juice and rind.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add remaining sugar to this.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into buttered dish.
Place into a pan of hot water and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
(You will discover when done that there will be cake at the top and delightful lemon sauce in the bottom.
Spoon the sauce over the cake when you serve it.)

title: chocolate pie
directions: Scald 1 1/2 cups milk.
Mix sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, 1/2 cup milk and beaten egg yolks.
Pour scalded milk over this mixture and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with egg whites, beaten stiff, allowing 2 tablespoons sugar to each egg white.
Brown in 325° oven.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all together for about 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Put
cherry
pie filling in 3 quart (9 x 13-inch) baking dish. Pour
and
spread
pineapple and juice over pie filling. Sprinkle dry
cake
mix over mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over
cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix these ingredients together.
When they are well blended, mix with starter.
Let mixture stand, out of refrigerator, lightly covered all day.
(Mixture will bubble.)
At the end of the day, take out 1 cup of starter to use in making bread.
Return other to refrigerator.
Keep covered.
Keep starter in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days and feed again.
Starter must be fed every 3 to 5 days. Always leave 1 cup of starter.
If you do not need to bake more bread after feeding starter, take 1 cup and give to a friend.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 12-inch pan or dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Add peaches, but do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream or milk.

title: bok choy salad
directions: Chop bok choy, cooked chicken and scallions; put in a large bowl.
Saute sesame seed, almonds and noodles in butter over low heat until slightly browned.
Put in a separate bowl.
Mix sugar, soy sauce, vinegar and seasoning; put this in a bowl.
Do not mix the 3 until ready to serve.

title: lazy golumbkies
directions: Chop cabbage.
Place half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix raw hamburger, cooked rice, diced tomato, chopped onion and brown sugar.
Spread over cabbage in pan.
Spread the rest of the cabbage on top and top all with tomato soup (you may need 2 cans). Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sour cream.
Stir in sugar, 2 Tbsp. flour, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in apples.

title: tortilla wrap
directions: Spread cream cheese on flour tortilla, then sprinkle green chillies on cream cheese and top with black olives.
Layer another tortilla on top and repeat steps; fold over in half.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill overnight.
Take out and slice in small bite size; put toothpicks in them.
Dip in salsa and enjoy.

title: pumpkin gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in molasses and egg. Add dry ingredients alternately with 1/2 cup water. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.

title: granola
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar, honey, vanilla and molasses.
Mix oats, coconut, cinnamon, almond, walnuts and sunflower seeds.
Stir both mixtures together in large pan until all is moist.
Spread out evenly onto 4 cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes until golden brown.
When granola is done, press down firmly into pan and allow to cool 1 hour.
When cool, break apart and store in airtight container.
Makes 4 to 5 gallons.
Bake longer for crunchy granola.
This is a summer camp recipe, make 1/4 recipe for family.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well; add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour mixture into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Stir whipped topping and cream cheese together.
Fold in pie filling and oranges.
Line bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with waxed paper.
Pour in cherry mixture.
Cover.
Freeze until firm.

title: baked beans(really good!!)
directions: Brown and drain the ground beef, bacon and onion.
Mix in a large bowl both sugars, catsup, mustard, barbecue sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in meat mixture.
Add one can of pork and beans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Can be frozen before or after baking.
Yields 12 servings.

title: mixed green salad
directions: In large bowl whisk oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add next five ingredients; toss well to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let cake cool slightly.
Using a wooden spoon handle, punch holes at 1-inch intervals over top of cake.

title: taco sauce
directions: Combine tomato paste, water, vinegar, corn syrup and spices and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, or until thick.
Stir frequently to avoid sticking.
Pour into hot jars leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust caps.
Process 30 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: sourdough buckwheat cakes
directions: Dissolve yeast in
cup
water.
Stir
in remaining water, flour and sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Cover with cheese cloth. Let stand at
room
temperature for 5 days, stirring a couple times each
day.
Cover
and refrigerate until ready to use, or use right away.
When ready to use, put in a crock and add amount of water
needed
to
make
cakes
enough
for your family.
Then add
pure buckwheat flour (not self-rising) and 1/2 white flour.
Add
salt to taste.
As you use you will need to add a little
sugar
to
each new crock you mix.
When not in use, set in
a
cool
place
and
keep covered.
Right before you bake cakes, add
1 cup warm water to which is added 1 teaspoon soda. Add more water to batter if too thick.
Bake on hot, greased griddle.

title: black bean soup
directions: Drain beans and cover with cold water.
Boil gently until tender; drain.
Saute ham, onions and pepper in olive oil in kettle.
Put beans back into kettle and add 5 cups of water, beef broth, chili powder, cayenne, garlic and cilantro.

title: ida's fantastic banana bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening, then add the beaten eggs.
Mash bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt with mashed bananas to the sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Grease a loaf pan (9 x 4 x 2-inch).
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: applesauce fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill.
Serve with fruit or fat-free cinnamon star cookies or cubes of angel food cake for a fat-free party food.

title: fruit dip
directions: Take insides out of fresh pineapple and pour juice into cream cheese.
Add marshmallow cream and stir until smooth.
Put mixture back into empty pineapple and serve with an assortment of fresh or canned fruit.
You can cut this recipe in half since it makes a bunch!

title: caramel biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12-cup fluted pan.
Combine brown sugar, nuts, oleo and water.
Heat until margarine melts. Separate biscuits into 20 individual biscuits.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Place in large bowl.
Pour brown sugar mixture over biscuits.
Toss lightly to mix evenly.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In shallow bowl, combine cracker meal, cumin and garlic powder.
Dip each chicken breast in egg, then coat with crumb mixture.
In large skillet, over medium-high heat saute chicken in margarine until golden brown on both sides.
Cover; reduce heat and cook 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve with salsa if desired.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Add cake mix, 1/3 at a time, mixing well after each addition. Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop batter by scant teaspoonfuls on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 cake
mix, oleo, brown sugar and water in large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top and bake 10 to 15 minutes, until marshmallows are golden.

title: amish cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Blend together buttermilk and baking soda.
Add to mixture, then add flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Mix well by hand.
Mixture will look like pancake batter.
Drop 1/4 cup of batter on cookie sheet (not greased).
Sprinkle dough with cinnamon and sugar.
(You will get 4 to 5 cookies per sheet.)
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Cut bread into 8 slices.
Combine eggs, milk, baking powder and vanilla; pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: just like fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in buttermilk.
Let set while you mix the other ingredients.
Then in a shaker bag, shake chicken and flour mixture until well coated.
Spray a baking dish with Pam and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
You may need to broil for 2 to 3 minutes when done.
This leaves a crispy crust just like frying, but it has no oil.

title: corn relish(salt free)
directions: Put the corn in a serving bowl, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Crunchy and colorful.
Great side dish to serve with sandwiches.
Will stay for 2 weeks in refrigerator if tightly sealed.

title: mashed potato candy(like mounds)
directions: In 8 x 8-inch glass dish lined with waxed paper, melt 1/2 chocolate chips and spread in bottom.
In bowl, mix potatoes and powdered sugar together.
Stir in coconut, vanilla and salt. Blend well.
Press over chocolate chips in glass dish.
Melt remaining chips and spread over potato mixture.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Add cheese and soup.
Stir until melted. Place broccoli in casserole dish; pour in soup mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Use craker crumbs for crust.

title: california marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients. This will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.
Marinate flank steaks or shish kabob meat 24 hours before grilling.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in casserole dish. Bake 50 minutes. Remove from oven. Mix crackers and oleo. Put on top of casserole. Return to oven for 10 minutes longer.

title: spicy noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except noodles, bacon and Parmesan cheese, in large mixing bowl.
Add noodles and bacon; toss until well mixed.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until heated through.
Remove cover; sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Broil until golden brown. Top with additional Parmesan cheese and sour cream.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Add the onions, oregano, salt, soup and water to meat. Layer the noodles, meat mixture and cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whirligig cookies
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Melt chocolate chips; cool slightly.
Spread on rolled out dough.
Roll up like jelly roll and chill.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: beef roast
directions: Brush roast with Kitchen Bouquet, completely covering all sides.
Place roast in baking dish large enough to add soup and water around roast.
Carefully seal roast completely in aluminum foil.
Cook in 300° oven, without opening roast, 4 hours or until done.
When the roast is done, the gravy is also made.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Take a chuck roast and boil in water for several hours or all day or overnight in a crock-pot.
Separate, discard fat and shred very thin.
To meat, add Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce, butter, sugar, onion powder or onion, catsup and chili sauce.
If more catsup is needed for right consistency, add it.
Heat and serve on buns.

title: donuts
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine; let cool to lukewarm.
Measure water (about 85°) into large mixing bowl. Crumble in yeast.
Add ginger; stir until yeast dissolves.
Add the lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and half the flour.
Beat about 5 minutes with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough, more flour might be necessary, but the less used the lighter the donuts.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured board; let stand for 5 minutes, then knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place dough into a well-greased bowl.
Turn to grease all sides.
Cover with plastic and a slightly dampened towel.
Let rise in warm place until dough is doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: beef jerky marinade
directions: Mix smoke, soy sauce and sugar in saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Remove from stove.
Add hot sauce and pepper.
Let stand about 15 minutes while you cut meat.
Place meat in marinade; secure lid. Let stand about 10 minutes, shaking and turning bowl to cover all pieces equally.
Drain.
Place on trays and dry in dehydrator according to directions for your dehydrator.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix well and shape into ball.
Ice ham ball with sour cream and put sliced olives on top.

title: punch
directions: This is best if it is prechilled.
A few ice cubes may be added to maintain coolness.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: irish brown soda bread
directions: Sift the flours, salt and baking soda into a large bowl. Stir in the oats. Make a well in the center, pour in the buttermilk and stir with a wooden spoon until the mixture comes together to form a soft, moist dough. If the dough seems too dry, add a few more tablespoons buttermilk.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook ground meat with chopped green pepper and onion until done.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Mix macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Mix all together in casserole and sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Good with a salad and French garlic bread.

title: best dessert
directions: Pour into round cake tin.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve with fresh strawberries and whipped cream.
Yum!

title: barley pilaf
directions: Drain the barley, then saute it in olive oil for 5 minutes over medium-high heat with the onion.
Add salt, pepper and beef broth.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce to a simmer and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until barley is just done.
Don't overcook or the barley will lose its nutty flavor.
Add parsley and nutmeg.
Toss and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Top with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, orange juice, egg and a small piece of butter. Cook until thick.
After it has cooled, add whipping cream to mix.
Split 2 sponge cakes in half, making 4 layers.
Top each layer and sides.
Refrigerate overnight or make in morning to serve at night.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown ground beef and onions, drain off fat. Stir in barbecue sauce, onions and brown sugar.
Heat until bubbly. Set aside. Separate biscuits and place each in a ungreased muffin cup.
Spoon meat mixture into each cup top with cheese and bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
This is so easy and so good.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, butter, milk, eggs, sugar, and vanilla. Mix topping of brown sugar, flour, butter, and walnuts and cover potato mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes.
tags: fresh cooked and mashed sweet potatoes

title: taco bean dip
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and mix as directed on package.
Add other ingredients in layers.
Top with grated cheese.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; rub skins with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Allow potatoes to cool to touch.
Cut a 1-inch strip, lengthwise, from top of each potato.
Scoop out pulp.
Combine pulp and all other ingredients, except cheese and bacon bits, in a small bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until lumps disappear. Stuff shells with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add cheese and bacon bits.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: braised beef
directions: Fry the slices of beef until medium brown.
Add onion, celery, carrots, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Add 2 cups water and let simmer until done (about 1 1/2 hours).
Serve over rice.

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
Beat egg whites with a dash of salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well. Then beat until soft peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and vinegar. Fold in chocolate and walnuts.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples; pour honey in center until filled.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Eat warm.

title: canadian cheese soup(1836 room original recipe - marilyn ritenour's version)
directions: Heat in double boiler.

title: dressing
directions: Bake at 350° until brown.

title: loaf o' gold
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or 2 loaf pans (8 x 4 x 2-inch) or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Mix everything together.
Bake for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, butter and egg.
Stir in 3 cups of flour.
Mix until smooth. Add enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover bowl tightly with foil.
Refrigerate for 2 to 24 hours.

title: apple spice cookies
directions: Combine sugars and butter.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Combine flour, oatmeal, spices and baking soda.
Add to sugar and butter mixture.
Stir in apples.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: english toffee
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Melt butter in saucepan. Add sugar and mix well.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix and bake in moderate oven.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan layer first with lettuce. Add other ingredients in order given.
Spread with mayonnaise. Top with cheese and bacon.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight (24 hours).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet and sour party meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in butter over medium heat or brown on broiler pan in oven.
Place meatballs in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine cornstarch, vinegar and sugar in a medium sized saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen (approximately).

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix and press into bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan.

title: chicken and broccoli biscuits
directions: Saute all ingredients, except cheese, in chicken broth until veggies are tender and broth evaporated. Roll biscuits to about 5-inch diameter. Place portion of chicken mix on flattened biscuit. Top with a little grated cheese. Fold biscuit over and crimp edges together with fork. Bake on cookie sheet according to directions on biscuit can.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 3 heaping tablespoons or 1/4 cup mixture; fill cup with water (put mixture in first).
Heat in microwave on Full power for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or to your liking.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Blend together 1 teaspoon flour, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar. Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture over unbaked pastry shell in a 9-inch pie pan.
Fill liberally with sliced apples.
Sprinkle with remaining flour mixture.

title: shrimp new orleans
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute all ingredients (except shrimp and wine) until vegetables are slightly tender.
Add shrimp and saute until pink (done but still tender).
Add wine.
Cover and cook 60 seconds longer.
Serve with rice.

title: two flavor fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring occasionally. Boil for 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Add Marshmallow Fluff and bits.
Stir until melted and mixture is smooth. Blend in walnuts and vanilla. Pour into 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Put frozen potatoes in greased casserole.
Combine and heat cheese, soup, onion, 1/4 lb. margarine and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes. Put corn flakes over the top and sprinkle 6 Tbsp. margarine over corn flakes. Bake 30 minutes covered and then 30 minutes uncovered in a 350 degree oven.

title: hobo potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Cut into wedges.
Put into desired size Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with salt and seasoned salt.
Top with onions and cut into wedges.
Use as many as desired.
Cut margarine into chunks.
Place over onions Use more than 1 stick if using extra large pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 1 hour or until tender.
Stir and serve hot.

title: pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix and press pretzels, margarine. and regular sugar in a 11 X 13 pan.
Bake at 350 for 8 minutes and cool.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl and chill until firm.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and celery in broth until tender; mash lightly. Add cream sauce made with half and half, margarine and flour. Add parsley; simmer to thicken.
Add green onions 10 minutes before serving.

title: orangy carrot and raisin salad
directions: Blend soft drink mix into mayonnaise.
Combine carrots, raisins and mayonnaise mixture, mixing well.
Chill about 1 hour; stir before serving.
Makes about 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: louisiana yam cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cloves, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine sugar and oil in a bowl.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, dry ingredients, yams and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook and drain rice.
Cook and drain sausage.
Saute onions in sausage fat.
Drain fat and add sausage and mushrooms.
Mix flour and cream until smooth.
Add chicken broth and cook until thick; add remaining seasoning.
Mix everything together in casserole pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with almonds.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken breasts and dice.
Roll out batter as thin as possible; cut into 1 x 3-inch strips.
Bring broth to boil, drop in strips and reduce to simmer.
Add cream of chicken soup, margarine and salt.
Cook about 20 minutes.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Place chicken in glass or plastic bowl.
Mix together remaining ingredients;
pour over chicken.
Let marinate, covered, in refrigerator several hours.
Grill or broil chicken, turning once, about 7 to 10 minutes on each side.
Baste with extra marinade.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone and cut into bite-size pieces. Mix chicken, grapes, chestnuts, celery and slivered almonds.
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, lemon juice and soy sauce; add to chicken and mix well.
Chill.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: springtime skillet dinner
directions: Brown in fat in 10-inch skillet the garlic clove.
Remove garlic.
Add onion and ground beef.
Cook until browned, stirring. Add rice and water.
Simmer uncovered over low heat for 40 minutes.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Continue simmering until tender (20 minutes).
Season with soy sauce, salt and pepper. Serve hot, garnished with parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Quarter apples.
Mix all together in crock-pot on high for 4 hours.
Stir and put on low for 12 hours.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Combine egg, buttermilk, sour cream and molasses.
Slowly stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in 3/4 cup blueberries.

title: taco appetizer
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese. Pour over hamburger.
Add tomatoes and green peppers.
Put jar of taco salsa on top.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then add pumpkin and milk. Stir to mix.
Add dry ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Drain tomatoes, reserving 3/4 cup juice. Cut tomatoes in quarters; stir into pasta with 1/2 teaspoon salt and thyme.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Trim fat from chops and brown chops.
Arrange over pasta, sprinkle with onions. Combine tomato juice, bouillon cube, salt and marjoram.
Heat to dissolve bouillon cube.
Pour over chops, cover and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Add green pepper, re-cover and bake 15 minutes more. Serves 6.

title: orange balls
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and orange juice. Add crushed vanilla wafers; mix well. Make small balls and roll in coconut. Makes 3 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan and warm.
Break 10 to 12 flour tortillas in pieces and dip in chicken broth.
Grease large baking dish and line with flour tortillas, sauce and cheese, making 2 layers ending with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted and bubbling, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian cheese pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Top with pineapple which has been cooked with cornstarch until thickened.

title: brunch casserole
directions: This may be assembled ahead of time.
Cover with foil and refrigerate.

title: cranberry loaf
directions: Chop cranberries. Mix all ingredients. Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lone star sixteen bean soup
directions: Cook all day (6 to 8 hours).
Add water if needed. Serve with cornbread and big spoons!

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until done.

title: buttered horn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in water.
Add remainder of sugar, shortening and salt.
Add eggs.
Stir in flour and beat well.
Add additional flour until stiff to stir with spoon.
Work down; divide into 4 parts.
Turn out on floured board, roll in circle and cut into 8 parts.
Roll up, starting with big end. Place on greased tin and let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: dina's jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello and Knox gelatin
in boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients (except sour cream).
Put 1/2 of the mixture in 8-9 inch corning dish or 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Chill until firm. Spread sour cream over.
Add other 1/2 of ingredients.
Chill until firm.
(You can also substitute raspberry jello and frozen raspberries in place of the strawberry.)

title: homemade baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl and put in pan for oven.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated broccoli appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except broccoli.
Add broccoli and marinate 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat in 5-quart pan with chopped onion; drain oil.
Add kidney beans, diced tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Stir well.
Add 2 to 4 cups water and taco seasoning mix plus salt.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or more.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Saute onion in oil in large skillet.
Add ground beef and brown.
Drain off grease.
Stir in soup, water chestnuts, mushroom, water, seasonings and cooked wild rice.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake covered for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter marshmallow fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream along with peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix and pour into a buttered dish.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and chop fine.
Mix with other ingredients (a food processor works well for this).
Turn mixture into buttered shallow casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with crackers or pita bread.
Serves 12.

title: the kids' favorite casserole
directions: Simmer chicken in a covered pot in a small quantity of water until tender.
Cool; remove meat from bones and cut in bite-size pieces.
Cut tortillas into 1-inch square pieces.
Combine all other ingredients except cheese.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, put layers of chicken, tortillas and soup mixture until all are used. Top with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before cooking.
Bake from 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 300° oven.
Serves 6.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift the flour, salt and baking powder into a bowl.
Add the egg, melted butter and corn.
Add enough water to make a very stiff mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot deep fat (360°).
Serve with maple syrup or chicken gravy.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gourmet rice krispie treats
directions: Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and salt in saucepan; bring to a full boil.
Stir in peanut butter; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, cereals and lastly, chocolate chips.
Quickly press into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: turkey n stuffing bake
directions: Combine butter and water; stir until butter melts.
Pour over seasoned stuffing crumbs; toss lightly.
Stir in 1/2 can fried onions.
Spoon stuffing mixture into 9-inch shallow baking dish. Press stuffing across bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients listed and bake for 45 minutes at 350° in a loaf pan.

title: sean's grandma's banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix in wheat germ.
Add remaining ingredients, beat until well blended.
Pour into 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: anchovy chip dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Use as a dip for crackers or potato chips.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together for about 10 minutes.
Add peanuts and continue cooking 15 minutes, until golden brown. Remove from fire.
Add soda and stir.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put mixture into a large punch bowl and serve.

title: chicken-noodle-spinach casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cool.
Debone and cut into small pieces.
Reserve broth to cook noodles.
Saute celery, green pepper and onions in small amount of margarine.
Combine chicken, sauteed vegetables, mushrooms with liquid, soup and cheese.
Add a bit of broth if it seems too thick, but be careful not to make it "soupy!"

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Slowly add flour alternately with the eggs and mix thoroughly.
Chill overnight.
Roll out thin on a lightly floured board.
Brush cool cookies with egg white which has been slightly beaten.
Sprinkle with sugar and press 1/2 pecan in center.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 17 dozen.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together (except chicken); cook in saucepan until it thickens.
Pour over chicken; bake for 1 hour.
Serve hot over steamed rice.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt oleo or butter in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread brown sugar over butter.
Then arrange pineapple slices and cherries as desired.
Prepare batter by creaming butter and sugar together.
Add egg.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn upside down on plate.

title: rosy red rhubarb cake
directions: Cut shortening into
sifted
dry
ingredients and brown sugar as for pie crust.
Add
egg
and
milk;
mix thoroughly. Spread in bottom and a little up
the
sides	of
a
x 9 x 2-inch pan; mixture will
be moist.
Top with rhubarb.	Sprinkle gelatin powder over.
Mix
butter
with sugar and flour as for pie crust. Sprinkle over
rhubarb.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: *I use 1 (15 3/4 ounce) jar fig preserves and 1 (4 ounce) jar of baby food peaches (or whatever kind you had rather use).

title: broccoli tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine all ingredients except tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Cover.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.
Before serving, add tomatoes and toss lightly. Garnish with olives and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 or more.

title: chewies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Gradually sift in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a medium size bowl; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream the butter with beater; add sugars gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate additions of the pumpkin and dry ingredients, mixing well by hand.
Add chocolate chips and nuts, mixing once again by hand.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake approximately 16 to 20 minutes.
Cookies are done when bottoms are golden.
Cool on wire racks.

title: dilly green tomato pickles
directions: Pack tomatoes in sterilized jars.
To each jar, add 1 clove garlic, 1 stalk celery and 1 hot green pepper.

title: punch
directions: Chill liquid ingredients before mixing.
Ice cubes made from more pineapple juice will keep the punch from diluting.
Makes approximately 40 (6 ounce) cups.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix all together and marinate beef for a minimum of 2 hours, turning occasionally.
Use for broiling or on the barbecue.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan over low heat, place soup, milk, margarine and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: basic chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a Dutch oven until meat is browned, stirring until it crumbles; drain.
Add 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally (10 minutes).
Add additional water, if necessary.
Makes 7 cups.

title: baked apple(microwave)
directions: Core apple and place in shallow baking dish; place cinnamon, nutmeg and diet margarine in core of apple.
Add 1/8 cup of water to dish and cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Bake in microwave 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 1.

title: chunky chocolate cookie squares
directions: In a large bowl, mix butter and sugar at low speed with mixer until fluffy.
Slowly beat in corn syrup, then egg and vanilla. Beat in flour until blended.
Stir in pecans and half of chocolate chunks.
Spread evenly in an ungreased 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Sprinkle remaining chocolate on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool, cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.

title: baked apple chunks
directions: Place apples in an 8 x 5-inch microwaveproof loaf dish. Combine brown sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Crumble over apples.
Dot with margarine.
Cook, covered, on High (maximum power) for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring once.
Serves 4.

title: louisiana chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients, including cocoa together, and add alternately with the milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan.
Pour in batter. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick tests done.
Do not overbake.
It's best to leave a little gooey on the inside.

title: fruit cocktail pie(low sugar)
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add ice cubes and let set until thickened. Take out unmelted ice. Add Cool Whip and drained fruit cocktail.
Mix together and put into graham cracker crust. Let set at least 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Drain asparagus.
Layer in baking dish noodles, asparagus, soup, cheese.
Repeat layers. Top with cheese and heat in oven a 350° until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple in casserole.
Cover with mixture of flour, sugar and cheese.
Crumble crackers in bowl and mix with melted oleo.
Cover top of casserole with this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fat man's misery
directions: Crush cookies.
Line 9-inch pie pan or 8-inch square pan with most of crushed Oreos (save some for top).
Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Cream again.
Add almond flavoring.
Spread on crumbs.
If using whipped cream, whip cream and sugar; add vanilla.
Mix pecans with whipped topping and spread on first mixture.
Cover with crushed Oreos. Let refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: peanut butter fingers(makes 4 dozen small bars)
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugars and cream well.
Blend in egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and rolled oats.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and powdered sugar.
Cut in butter.
Press mixture in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine sugar, 1/4 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs.
Blend well.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Spread this mixture over the partially baked dough.
Return to oven.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in bars. Yield: 24 bars.

title: grilled mozzarella
directions: Place Mozzarella cheese slices on half of bread slices, trimming cheese to fit.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Combine eggs, milk, thyme and salt.
Dip both sides of sandwiches in egg mixture, then dip in bread crumbs.
Press crumbs lightly so that they will adhere.
Saute on lightly greased griddle over medium-high heat for about 8 minutes, or until crisp, turning once.
Serve warm.
Makes 16 appetizers.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate-peanut butter squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread cookie dough on bottom of 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, evenly over warm crust. In small bowl, blend powdered sugar, peanut butter and milk. Place spoonfuls of peanut butter mixture on top of chocolate chips and swirl to marble.
Cool completely.
Makes 24 squares.

title: crabmeat puffs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Spread on split muffins and freeze at least 15 minutes.
Store in freezer until ready to use.
Broil and serve quartered for appetizers.

title: lentil soup
directions: Saute onions and carrot in oil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add thyme and marjoram and saute 1 minute more.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer until tender (several hours).
Good topped with grated white cheese or sour cream.

title: moma's casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to directions on bag.
Brown ground beef and onion until done; drain excess oil from ground beef.
Add can of mushroom soup and 1/2 can of water to ground beef and onions; simmer 10 minutes on low heat and add to cooked egg noodles.
Sour cream can be added to individual servings, if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and quarter Irish potatoes; place in casserole dish. Sprnkle diced onions over potatoes.
Dribble melted oleo over potatoes and onions.
Pour chicken broth over mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over mixture.
Bake 45 min. or until potatoes are tender, in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate crispy cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat oleo and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour mixture.
Stir in cereal and chips.

title: crescent veggie squares
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Put edges together and seal perforations by pinching and pressing with fingers.
Pat or roll out to rectangle shape 13 x 15-inch.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: bridesmaid salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add undrained fruit, marshmallows and cheese; let cool.
Add mayonnaise and whipping cream.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 50 two inch squares.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Manwich) and make into meat balls. Pour oil in a skillet and brown the meat balls.
Put meat balls in deep dish and put a can of Manwich over them.
Cover meat balls and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: holly taters
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes. Wash potatoes well and cut into 6 to 8 wedges each.
Place in mixture in plastic bag. Add potatoes, a few pieces at a time.
Shake to coat each side. Place in baking pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over top. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: mom's chili
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Add rest and simmer 1 hour.

title: amazing coconut pie(makes its own crust.)
directions: Just mix, bake and serve.

title: easy caramel sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; mix well. Cook over medium heat until mixture reaches 200°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter, whipping cream and vanilla.
Serve sauce warm over ice cream or pound cake.
Makes 3 cups.

title: lemon raspberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees.
Line 16 muffin cups with paper baking cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
In small bowl, combine half-and-half, oil, lemon extract and eggs.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir just until ingredients are moistened.
Carefully fold in raspberries.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 425 degrees for 18-23 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts; debone.
Cook broccoli.
Grease 11 x 7-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan; add drained broccoli.
Combine undiluted chicken soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Put all ingredients in large pan; cover with water.
Boil 3 to 4 hours or until tender.
Let stand in broth in refrigerator overnight.
Slice meat; return to broth and heat.
Serve with pepperoncini peppers.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Prepare taco meat (ground beef and taco seasoning) as per package instructions in a large pot.
To this, add and stir in tomato sauce and paste, salsa and brown sugar.
Next, add red pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles and sprinkle cheese over the top.

title: seafood medley casserole
directions: Mix seafood and place in a greased casserole dish.
Pour soup over seafood.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or pasta.

title: beef zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini (do not peel) into 1 inch cubed pieces and cook in boiling salt water until barely tender.
Drain well.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add salt and cooked rice to beef mixture. Place 1/2 of zucchini in 3 quart dish (casserole).
Spread beef mixture over zucchini.
Cover with cottage cheese; then add the remaining zucchini.
Spread mushroom soup over the zucchini--top with butter bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: simple lasagna(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease baking pan and set aside. Brown meat in a skillet and drain off grease. Add sauce and water to ground beef - simmer for 10 minutes. Put 1/3 of the sauce in the bottom of the baking pan, lay uncooked noodles on top of sauce, in a single layer. Spoon 1/2 of cheese on top of the noodles. Be sure the cheese covers most of the noodles. Pay attention to the edges. Sprinkle 1/2 of the Mozzarella on top of the ricotta cheese. Put 1/3 of the sauce on top of the mozzarella, then repeat layers again. The final layer should be sauce. Sprinkle parmesan cheese on the top. Cover the pan with foil. Bake for 50 minutes at 350 degrees. Let set for about 10 minutes before serving.

title: italian coffee cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Save 3/4 cup mixture for topping.
Add all remaining ingredients except cinnamon and mix until most of the lumps are dissolved.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 inch square pans or round cake pans.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon and swirl with knife.
Sprinkle on reserved topping mixture.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: minced clam appetizers
directions: Drain most of the liquid from the can of clams and mix with cream cheese and a dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on crackers or toast to serve.
Especially good if placed under a broiler until tops are bubbly and brown.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add milk.
Then add other ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can be made a day ahead and refrigerated.
If refrigerated, bake 10 minutes longer.

title: jello mold salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Set aside until slightly firm. Blend all remaining ingredients into Jell-O.
Spray mold or container with Pam or grease slightly.
Pour Jell-O mixture into container; set in refrigerator until firm.

title: chocolate chewies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach pineapple chiffon
directions: Put pineapple in saucepan and let come to boil; add jello and dissolve real well.
Let cool.
Whip with mixer.
Add cold buttermilk and whip again.
Add Cool Whip and beat again real well.
Put in dish and let congeal.

title: creamy garlic sauce
directions: In a small skillet cook garlic in butter over low heat about 5 minutes or until garlic is golden.
Put in blender or food processor.
Add mayonnaise and pepper; process until smooth.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Combine the graham crackers, 6 tablespoons melted butter and 6 tablespoons powdered sugar to make crust.
Put in square casserole dish.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix well sugar, eggs and oil, adding eggs, one at a time.
Add pumpkin.
Sift together cinnamon, baking powder, allspice, soda, salt and flour.
Add this to the first mixture, about one-third cup at a time and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Put in cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: slop cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ham balls and noodles
directions: Combine ham, bread crumbs, onion, dill, milk, mustard, egg and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In a large skillet, heat oil and margarine.
Brown ham balls.
Remove ham balls to serving platter or dish.
(Can be put in a baking dish and baked in a 325° oven.)
Blend flour into ham drippings; gradually add water and stir until thick and smooth.
Add sour cream and pepper.
Heat through, but do not boil.
Place noodles on platter; cover with ham balls.
Pour sauce over ham balls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 24 hour refrigerator salad
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and eggs.
Cook slowly until mixture thickens, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Cool.
Pack vanilla wafer crumbs in flat pan or dish.
Spread cooked filling over crumbs, then spread 1/2 cream over filling.
Arrange mashed apricots on cream. Sprinkle with nuts.
Spread on remaining whipped cream.
Sprinkle top with wafer crumbs.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry. Brush the inside with white of egg.
Chill.
Beat eggs slightly with fork; add the sugar and salt; stir until blended.
Add milk and cream; blend well.
Gently pour custard into pie pan. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: heavenly bits
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Form into marble-sized balls.
Place close together on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Makes about 75 cookies.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix together cocoa, flour, sugar and milk; cook slowly until thicken, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter, stirring gently until cool and thick enough to spread.

title: strawberry orange delight
directions: In medium bowl, stir in boiling water into jello. at least 2 minutes or until completely dissolved. Stir in cold water. Refrigerate about 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened. Reserve a few oranges for garnish if desired. Gently stir in remaining oranges in thickened jello. In a separate bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar with wire whisk until well blended. Gently stir in 2 cups whipped topping. Spoon into large serving bowl; cover with jello mixture. Refrigerate 2 hour or until firm. Garnish with remaining whipped topping and oranges. Yield 16 servings.

title: spiders
directions: In a double boiler, melt butterscotch chips.
Remove from heat.
Add cashews and chow mein noodles.
Mix well.
Use teaspoon to spoon out on wax paper.
Set in refrigerator for about 15 minutes.

title: 14 day pickles
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Pour over cukes.
Let set for 8 days (skim if necessary).
Drain.

title: german chocolate snack cake
directions: Stir together cake mix, 1 egg, pecans and butter; press mixture into bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Beat sugar, cream cheese and remaining 3 eggs at medium speed with mixture until creamy. Spoon powdered sugar mixture over batter in pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Cool and cut into 2 to 3-inch square. Serve with ice cream or put Cool Whip on top.

title: ham and potato scallop
directions: Cut ham in serving or bite-sized pieces.
Place half potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with ham pieces.
Place remaining potatoes on top.
Combine soup, milk, green pepper, onion and pepper.
Pour over potatoes and dot with butter.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover; bake 45 minutes longer or until potatoes are done.

title: prune pudding
directions: Cook prunes in 2 1/2 cups water until soft.
Remove stones. Make 1 package of gelatin according to directions.
Add prunes and 1/4 cup of almonds or walnuts.
Let set and serve with whipped cream.
Serves six.

title: no-bake cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Add sugar and beat. Add Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill.
Top with cherries or other pie filling.

title: carol's corn casserole
directions: Mix together in greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Bake at least 45 minutes in a 350 degree oven.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese together.
Add and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and freeze.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Add soups, Ro-Tel and enchilada sauce to drained ground beef.
Warm to a slow boil. Layer tortilla chips, mixture and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: english cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cookies will feel firm to touch.

title: dark chocolate pie
directions: Prepare pudding according to packaged directions and chill. Mix the cream cheese with 1/2 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread mixture in the bottom of the pie shell.
Once pudding is chilled, pour it over the cream cheese mixture.
Top the pie with a generous amount of Cool Whip.
For optional garnish, take an additional Skor bar and grate it over the top of the Cool Whip.
Cool overnight.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice squash, peppers and onions paper thin. Mix together first 4 ingredients. Let stand 3 hours, rinse and drain. Mix together next 6 ingredients. Heat to boiling point. Add squash mixture and bring to boiling point again. Do not boil. Put in jars and seal.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, Bisquick, eggs, butter and vanilla in a blender.
Blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let mixture stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Toss together all except cheese and potato chips.
Put cheese and chips on top.
Bake long enough to melt cheese, about 10 minutes, in a 400° oven.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salted boiling water until tender; drain. Saute onion in 5 tablespoons of butter.
Add soup mixture and mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir into cabbage, salt and pepper. Melt butter until browned; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in uncovered dish.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Chop onions, celery and green pepper.
Mix together and chill.

title: never fail pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and pumpkin in large bowl.
Slowly add milk and dry ingredients.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool. Garnish, if desired, with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: popovers(dutch biscuits)
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Divide the butter into a popover pan, or muffin pan and melt in oven.
Beat eggs until foamy, add flour and milk and blend for 1 minute.
Full pan with batter, bake for 10 minutes, reduce oven temp to 350 degrees and bake for 10 more minutes.
DO NOT OPEN THE OVEN WHILE BAKING! These will be really big, fluffy rolls, they will flop if you open the oven.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix, spoon over chicken and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecued potatoes
directions: Put raw potatoes, thinly sliced, in a large skillet.
Cover with milk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour or until potatoes are cooked.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine flour, nuts and melted butter.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill until firm.

title: monster toast
directions: Pour milk into a cup.
Add food coloring (red, blue, yellow or green).
Paint a monster on bread.
Put in toaster and toast. Butter lightly.
Eat and enjoy!

title: potato dumplings with ham
directions: Cook ham or pork hocks in water for about 1 hour or 20 minutes in a pressure cooker.
Mix flour and potatoes.
Drop by spoonfuls into ham water and cook about 40 minutes.
Serve with butter.

title: salsa(mike's)
directions: Stir ingredients with fork, then put on lowest setting of blender.
Add more salt or jalapeno to taste.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
Heat a frypan and rub with 1 teaspoon canola oil. Cook chicken until golden brown. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Serve with cooked pasta or rice. Serves 2.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together in medium glass bowl pineapple, mandarin oranges and dry jello.
Add to this cottage cheese and cool whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in 3/4 c. nuts.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Put apples, raisins and water in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cinnamon and salt over fruit.
Toss to combine.
Combine flour, oats, sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Spread over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until apples are tender. Sprinkle cheese over warm crisp.

title: tomato and broccoli bake
directions: Thaw broccoli, if frozen.
In a large kettle, cook pasta, uncovered, in boiling salted water for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain and set aside.

title: tuna pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add onion, garlic, celery, corn and black pepper and cook approximately 5 minutes.
Blend in flour, chicken broth and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add cheese, mustard and lemon juice.
Remove from heat.
Blend in tuna.

title: recipe for a blessing
directions: Mix together.
Season with fellowship and Christian love and serve on Thursday at 1:30 p.m. in meeting God's people.

title: shirley's diabetic cookie bar
directions: Cook raisins and water until water absorbed.
Let cool completely.
Sift all dry ingredients twice.
Mix applesauce, egg substitute and vanilla into raisins.
Add dry ingredients.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable spray.
Spread mixture.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: leann's microwave fudge
directions: Melt chips and condensed milk in microwave until melted and smooth.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a pan lined with wax paper and cool.
You can vary flavor with different chips (vanilla chips with maraschino cherries and pecans or peanut butter chips). When cold and set, turn out on cutting board.
Peel off wax paper and cut.

title: oven fried okra
directions: Wash okra and drain.
Remove tips and stem ends; cut okra crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine egg substitute and buttermilk; stir in okra and let stand 10 minutes.
Combine cornmeal and next 3 ingredients in a zip-top plastic bag.
Drain okra, small portions at a time, using a slotted spoon.
Place okra in bag with cornmeal mixture, shaking gently to coat.
Brush oil on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; add okra in a single layer.

title: mike's lasagna
directions: Boil noodles according to directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Brown meat.
Drain grease.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and oregano.
Mix Ricotta cheese with egg.
Spoon a little Ragu on bottom of a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch (3-quart) baking dish. Layer 1/2 noodles, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, meat and Ragu.
Make 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: sausage patties
directions: Shape sausage into patties.
Dip in eggs.
Roll in corn flakes.
Put Crisco into skillet; add patties and fry slowly until golden brown on each side.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat with onion; season with salt.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Separate rolls and spread in greased 10-inch pie pan.
Press together to form crust.
Sprinkle half of corn chips over crust.
Spoon meat mixture into crust. Spread sour cream over meat mixture.
Cover with cheese and remaining chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain.
Put sour cream, mayo, soup mix, and green onions together and mix.
Add spinach and mix again. Add chestnuts and refrigerate 2 hours before serving for best flavor. Serve in large round sourdough bread with center cut out or wheat thin crackers.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Place flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large mixing bowl with a pastry blender.
Work Crisco into dry ingredients until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Gradually mix in milk and dry yeast that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup lukewarm water. Mixture should be fairly thin.
Add flour until mixture can be kneaded.
Place dough on board and continue adding flour as necessary to be able to knead without dough sticking to board. Place in refrigerator at least 4 hours, better if overnight.
Roll out dough.
Cut biscuits with biscuit cutter and allow to rise 1 to 2 hours before cooking in 400° oven.
Cook for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs, oil and 7-Up, mixing well. Bake at 300° until well done in 3 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: strawberry omelet
directions: Beat eggs with water and salt.
Pour into hot skillet with butter melted over bottom.
Cook over medium-high heat until egg liquid is set.
Dash with cinnamon and nutmeg and spoon jam over eggs.
Fold half of omelet over jam and flip to other side to cook.
Slide omelet onto plate.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy with 1 stick butter over low heat.
Cream softened butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Blend in chocolate.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Beat in flour alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla; blend in candy and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan about 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Cool on rack 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: smoothie delite
directions: Put everything into a blender and whip until smooth.
The frozen banana really makes it taste like ice cream!
Serves 2.
If you add the protein powder, the taste may be affected. Most kids won't like it, but it is healthier.
Enjoy!

title: stuffed sweet potato
directions: Bake the potatoes; scoop out the centers and add salt, butter and cream to soften.
Refill the skins and bake in hot oven for about 5 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry and drain beef and bacon.
Mix all ingredients together in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Pour milk into top of double boiler and cook until it almost comes to a boil.
Slowly add corn meal, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture is thick and smooth, approximately 1 minute.
Add butter and salt and cool slightly.
Beat yolks and add to corn meal mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into corn meal. Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake in preheated 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until puffed and well browned.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water. Add 1/2 cup cold water; set aside at room temperature. Mix and bake cake as directed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan which has been greased and floured. Cool cake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Beat together eggs, 1/2 cup milk and salt.
Layer bread strips.
Add raisins to taste.
Pour egg and milk evenly over bread; pat down. Top with cinnamon and sugar. Bake for 25 minutes. Serve cold with whipped cream.

title: mocha brownie torte(rich and delicious)
directions: Grease and flour 2 round cake pans.
Blend brownie mix, water and eggs.
Stir in pecans.
Spread in pans and bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool thoroughly.

title: cheese fondue(serves 6)
directions: Dredge cheese with flour.
Rub cooking utensil with garlic. Pour in wine; set over low heat.
When wine is heated to the point that air bubbles rise to the surface, add cheese by handfuls, stirring constantly with wooden fork or spoon.
Keep stirring until cheese is melted.
Add Kirsch at this time along with the salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Serve bubbling hot.

title: chocolate angel cake
directions: In medium glass bowl, combine chips, butter, corn syrup and 2 tablespoons of water.
Microwave on High for 1 3/4 minutes or until chips are melted.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Layer graham crackers on bottom of pan.
Put pudding mixture on top, another layer of graham crackers, another layer of pudding, another layer of graham crackers.
(Leave graham crackers whole.)
Spread mix on top of crackers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: squash pie
directions: Bake squash in covered baking dish about 30 minutes at 375° (Pam your dish).
Press through sieve into medium bowl (makes about 2 1/2 cups).
Combine butter, 2 tablespoons syrup and nuts in a pie plate and bake about 10 minutes, stirring to coat at 375°.
Cool.
Prepare your favorite pastry in a 9-inch pie plate. Line pastry and weight with pastry weights or dry beans and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove weights and brush with egg white and bake another 8 minutes, until golden brown.
Reduce oven to 350°.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1/4 cup butter.
Cook broccoli as directed and add 1/4 cup butter.
Mix soup, milk and cheese. Heat.
Add rice and mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes in a covered casserole.

title: campbell's golden chicken with noodles
directions: Mix soup, water, lemon juice, mustard, garlic and carrots in slow cooker.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 8 hours or until done.
Or you can cook on high 4-5 hours. Serve over noodles.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with a tossed green salad.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Cut lettuce, onion and tomatoes up. Layer in a 10 x 13-inch pan the nacho chips, meat, beans, onion and nacho cheese.
Bake in 330° oven for about 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and add cheese, tomatoes, lettuce and sour cream.

title: chicken divan
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken.
Cook vegetables only half of cooking time on directions; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, mix together the soup, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetables.
Place chicken on top of vegetables.
Cover with sauce; sprinkle light coating of bread crumbs on top.
Cook, uncovered, for about 45 minutes.
Add cheese to top; cook until melted.
Great served over rice!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix half of the sugar with peaches and pour into an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Melt butter.
Mix the other half of the sugar and the rest of the ingredients together.
Pour over butter. Pour on top of peaches and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
These may be frozen and used later.
Wrap in foil. Store and heat when needed.

title: old country dressing
directions: Shake all except oil together in a quart jar until salt and sugar are dissolved.
Fill bottle with salad oil.

title: gold brick's or "congo bars"
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Cut into little squares.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix together the eggs first, then zucchini last.
Pour into greased casserole, oblong or round (for thicker mixture).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into bite size strips; saute in butter until brown. Add onion, Season-All, nutmeg and sherry.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Have sour cream at room temperature.
Stir into cooled beef mixture and heat on low heat until hot, careful not to allow to boil (boiling will result in a curdled appearance).
Serve with white rice or buttered noodles.

title: onion bread
directions: Use very warm water for dry yeast.
Sprinkle yeast into water and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and 2 cups flour.
Stir, then mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup more flour, reserving 1/2 cup for kneading.
Knead until smooth and satiny (15 minutes).
Add remaining flour as needed.
Put in greased bowl and turn once.
Cover and let rise about 1 hour.
Punch down and divide.
Pat each half into greased cake pans.
Sprinkle with onion and let rise until doubled (45 minutes).
Melt butter.
Pour over dough and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place hash browns in bottom of pan. Mix together onion, salt, chicken soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and 1 stick of butter.
Top with crushed corn flakes and drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat chicken gravy
directions: In a small saucepan, stir together 1 1/3 cups of evaporated milk, the chicken bouillon and pepper.
Stir the remaining milk and flour together until well blended, then add to mixture in saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook another minute.
Makes 6 (1/4 cup) servings.

title: roberta's pasta salad
directions: Break pasta in half.
Cook according to package directions; drain and set aside.
In large bowl, combine pasta, green pepper, onion, carrot, pepperoni and cheeses.
Set aside.

title: italian meatball soup
directions: Combine al ingredients in large pan. Bring to boil; Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for about 10 minutes or until meatballs are heated.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix jello, hot water and frozen orange juice.
Whip after set. Fold in whipping cream and mandarin oranges.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
May sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts on top.

title: dixie chicken
directions: Saute celery and
pepper
in
a little oleo.
Add soup, milk and
pimento.
Heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat
and pour into greased or sprayed with Pam 1 1/2
quart casserole.
Bake in 450° oven 15 minutes or until bubbling all over.

title: cracker snack
directions: Mix all ingredients in cake pan (13 x 15-inch).
Bake 15 minutes in 325° oven.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, simmer until potatoes are tender (about an hour).
To thicken, mash some of the potatoes and stir.
To thin, add more milk or water.

title: refrigerator date-nut pinwheels
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; cook over low heat until thick.
Mix ingredients as usual; divide into 3 parts.
Roll out on floured wax paper.
Spread with date mixture; sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Roll like jelly roll.
(I use the waxed paper to roll with, as the dough is so rich.) Refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin and bake in a 350° oven.

title: pineapple mandarin salad
directions: Mix 1 cup pineapple juice with 1 box instant pudding. Pour over fruit and chill for 2 or 3 hours.

title: dad's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add vanilla. Add eggs and beat 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in flour, soda and salt. Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes only. Put wax paper on cookie sheet before baking.
Do not reuse wax paper.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: lemon lush
directions: Combine flour, butter and nuts.
Mix well and put into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust. Combine pudding mix and milk and heat until thick.
Put on top of cream cheese layer.
Top with additional Cool Whip.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Note: May substitute 2 teaspoons celery salt instead of paprika.

title: fancy fruit vinegar
directions: Wash fruit, pit cherries if using, but leave fruit whole. Place fruit in bottom of clean, sterilized jar.
Sterilize by immersing in boiling water for a few minutes.
Warm vinegar in an enameled pan, but do not boil.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix the remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fruit cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Measure flour, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, milk, eggs, vanilla and baking powder.
Mix at low speed until just mixed.
Increase speed to high and beat 3 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together well and pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: In large kettle, cook ribs in water until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Skim off foam.
Remove ribs from broth and strain broth. Refrigerate.
Remove meat from bones and set aside.
When broth is chilled, remove fat.
Return to heat.
Add potatoes, carrots, salt and pepper.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add sauerkraut, sausage and rib meat.
Simmer until heated through.
Meanwhile, cook bacon until crisp.
Strain off grease, reserving 1 tablespoon of bacon drippings.
Cook onion in drippings until onion is tender. Add to soup.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes more.
Garnish with bacon. (A little Parmesan is also great.)

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal or crumbs.
Make a well in flour mixture and stir in enough milk to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of the bowl and sticks to a fork.
Turn onto lightly floured surface and knead gently, about 15 minutes.
Roll 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter; lift biscuits to ungreased baking sheet.
Place close together for soft sides or an inch apart for crusty sides.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve at once.
Makes 12 to 16 biscuits.

title: ham and potato breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the paprika in a large bowl; pour into ungreased 8 X 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: relish
