directions: Combine sugar, celery seed, mustard seed, turmeric, vinegar and water in large pot. Add vegetable mixture, stir well. Bring to a boil and reduce heat. Simmer 3 minutes and seal in jars.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream together flour, butter or margarine and powdered sugar. Press into an 8 or 9-inch square pan, build up sides of pan slightly.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, soda and vanilla by hand.
Add pineapple with juice.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Pour off excess fat.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and mushroom soup.
Heat to simmer stage.
Put Fritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour meat-soup mixture over this, then cover with grated cheese and cook in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: mini-nut muffins
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with fork.
Grease mini size muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 24 mini muffins.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Saute onions and butter until tender. Add flour and cornstarch, blending well. Add stock and milk gradually. Stir constantly. When boiling, add carrots, celery, paprika and cheese. Cook over low heat until cheese is melted. Add salt if necessary.

title: six-bean casserole
directions: Form Italian sausage into 1-inch balls and brown in skillet. Drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients except bacon in 5-quart casserole.
Partially cook bacon and lay on top of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 16 servings. Great for picnics.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Cook in 3/4 cup water until tender. Drain; add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and melted butter.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour and salt.
Fold in coconut or nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until done.
Don't overbake.

title: kick back casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage. Drain grease. In a large buttered casserole dish, add frozen hash browns. Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 c. water, mix and heat with salsa or Rotels about 2 minutes. Pour over hash browns, pour onions and bell pepper over hash browns & soup. Next sprinkle browned sausage over casserole. Top with grated cheese. Place in 350° oven and bake for 40 minutes. Lets cool, Kick Back and Enjoy!

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed, adding 1 1/2 packages coconut and 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Bake as directed.
While cake is hot, poke holes with fork.
Heat milk, sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Pour over cake while hot.
Cool.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend together peanut butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with peanuts or chocolate curls.

title: corn chowder
directions: Boil potatoes in water until cooked.
Dice 1 small onion and saute in butter.
Drain potatoes and put into a pot with 2 cans creamed corn and onion.
Pour milk over mixture, about 1-inch more than potatoes, etc.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(Optional: Fry bacon until crisp.
Crumble and add to soup.)
Bring to hot, not boil, because of milk.

title: corn meal dumplngs
directions: Cook mustard greens with salt and oil to taste.
Boil in plenty of water.
Mix dry ingredients well.
Stir in egg and onion.
Add enough water to make a stiff dough.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls into boiling green liquid and cook slowly for about 15 minutes. Serve with pork roast and the greens.

title: friendship cake
directions: Combine 1 cup starter, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup chunk peaches. (Let stand 2 weeks.)

title: vegetable-cheese lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles as per package directions.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat margarine.
Add mushrooms and saute 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from heat and set aside.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix well and drop in muffin tins (about 2/3 full).
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; continue beating until light.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat well after each egg.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Beat well after each time.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Place into a cold oven.
Set temperature at 325°; bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until done.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: turkey burgers
directions: In a medium bowl, combine ground turkey, corn meal, cumin, chili powder, salt, pepper, lime juice, egg white and jalapeno pepper; mix lightly. Shape into 5 (1/2-inch thick) patties. Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until oil sizzles, about 1 minute. Add turkey patties. Cook 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until browned and no longer pink in center. Meanwhile, in small saucepan, combine and heat corn and salsa. Serve with turkey burgers. Serves 5.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place into a 9 x 10-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: farmer's potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins until almost done; do not overcook.
Peel and allow potatoes to cool, then grate or shred finely.
Place 1/3 of potatoes in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish; top with 6 to 8 thin pats of butter and a generous sprinkling of seasoned salt.
Repeat with 2 more layers. Pour unwhipped whipping cream over potatoes and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
The whipping cream will not cover potatoes, but will bubble up during cooking.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, cracker crumbs, onion, milk, egg and next 4 ingredients; gently shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meatballs.
Remove meatballs from skillet; pour off fat.

title: butter bite hoecakes
directions: Combine corn meal and boiling water; stir to blend.
In large skillet, heat 1/4-inch shortening over medium heat until a drop of water sizzles when dropped in skillet.
Spoon batter by tablespoonful into hot skillet.
Fry until golden brown; turn and fry on other side until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter. Makes about 10 hoecakes.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Combine brown sugar, sugar, catsup, mustard, molasses, chili powder and salt in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add onion, ground beef and bacon. Stir in beans. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May simmer overnight in a slow cooker. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: maxine's potatoes
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Cool and slice potatoes. Mix together with chicken soup and mushroom soup.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 cup cheese.
Add celery and onion.
Add milk.
Mix well.

title: strawberry jam-cheddar ring
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and chill.
An hour before serving, shape cheese mixture into a ring and scoop strawberry preserves into center.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: In a large pan, put peppers, sugar and vinegar and bring to a full rolling boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and let mixture simmer 10 minutes.
Line colander or strainer with 4 thickness of cheesecloth.

Place over bowl and strain mixture through it. Discard chopped peppers; return pepper liquid to pot and add about 9 drops of food coloring or enough to give a bright color; add pectin to colored liquid.
Stir well.
Bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat and boil 11 minutes.
Immediately pour into hot, dry and sterilized half pint or pint jars.
Seal while hot.
Makes 8 pints.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook peppers in boiling water 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients (except soup) and stuff peppers.
Pour over soup and 1/2 cup of water.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: no crust sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except whipped cream) in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Spoon mixture into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Wash potatoes and boil with jackets on.
When done, cut lengthwise in half.
Make small slits in potato and sprinkle with salt, pepper and melted butter to taste.
Dip potato in barbecue sauce and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Good hot or cold.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Place all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix well.
Place in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chilean salad
directions: Peel the tomatoes; cut in pieces like orange sections.
Soften the sliced onion by leaving it in water with salt and a spurt of vinegar for 15 minutes.
Rinse with water and drain.

title: venison-noodle skillet
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat in shortening.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery until transparent. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Cover tightly and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and carrots until tender.
Drain and mash. Add other ingredients and half of the dressing.
Mix other dressing with 1/2 stick margarine.
Put on top and bake until brown on top.

title: crab imperial
directions: Melt butter; mix in flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly until it boils and thickens.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread; cool.
Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In separate pan, beat margarine.
Add crab.
Combine with sauce.
Sprinkle paprika.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon ice cream pie
directions: Mix first 3
ingredients
well	and press against sides and bottom of
9-inch
pie
pan.
Chill.
Mix lemonade and ice cream well and place in cornflake crust.	Before serving, heat lemon rind and water
at a boil for 10 minutes.
Add sugar and cook 5 minutes
more,
stirring
to
melt sugar.
Drizzle over pie.

title: healthy sour cream cake(fat-free)
directions: Mix applesauce, egg whites and sugar.
Add baking powder, baking soda, vanilla, sour cream and flour.
Blend well.
Grease tube pan.
Put 1/2 the batter in.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar (raisins, if desired).
Put in rest of batter and sprinkle cinnamon/sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: german brownies
directions: Sift together
sugar and flour.
Mix in saucepan water, oil and cocoa.
Put
on
stove
and
bring to boil.
Pour over flour and
sugar.
Add eggs, well beaten, buttermilk and soda. (I use plain milk with 1 tablespoon vinegar.) Your batter will be real thin.
Bake
in oven at 375° for 25 minutes.
Pan size 12 x 8 1/2-inches or 15 x 10-inches.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Place aluminum foil in 9 x 13-inch pan, then sprinkle on dry soup mix.
Place the steak on top of the soup; pepper it.
(Be sure to trim off excess fat.)
Pour the undiluted mushroom soup over the steak, covering all the steak.
(I even add a little water because this will become gravy.) Place a sheet of aluminum foil over the top and seal the edges so well that none of the juices can escape.
(Don't peek in.)
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: chickpeas and pasta
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add macaroni.
Cook 8 minutes.
Lower heat to simmer.
Add both cans of chickpeas.
(Do not drain.) Simmer 2 minutes.
Sprinkle liberally with cheese.
Serve.

title: chicken a la queen
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onions in melted butter for one minute. Add remaining ingredients, except chicken. Cook over medium low heat, stirring frequently until cheese is melted. Add chicken. Heat through. Serve over country bread, cut one inch thick and broiled lightly on one side. Place bread on serving plate, toasted side down and top with sauce. Puff pastry, English muffins and biscuits may also be used.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare rice and broccoli separately.
Do not overcook broccoli.
In a casserole dish, mix rice, broccoli, mushrooms, butter and salt, then mix in mushroom soup and cheese.
Add a little cheese to the top of the casserole.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, milk and flavoring.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and flatten with hands.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° until light golden brown.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, egg, margarine, cracker crumbs, onion and
bell
pepper; put into a casserole.
Combine 1 cup cracker crumbs
and
melted margarine; sprinkle over mixture. Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: recipe for a happy kitchen
directions: Take love and loyalty, mix thoroughly with faith.
Blend in tenderness.
Add friendship and hope.
Fold in forgiveness. Sprinkle with laughter.
Bake in the warm sunshine of God's love. Serve generous portions among family members daily.

title: hamburger balls
directions: Heat catsup and spices.
Drop in meatballs.
Cook over medium heat approximately 45 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Place Crisco into cast iron skillet until melted or bubbling hot.
Mix all ingredients and pour into melted Crisco.
Bake until thoroughly cooked and brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepperoni together.
Add spaghetti sauce and Season-All; simmer about an hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil spaghetti and drain.
Put 1/2 spaghetti in bottom of a casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 spaghetti sauce and 1/2 shredded cheese.
Add the rest of spaghetti, then remaining sauce.
Top with balance of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat sweet potatoes and butter with electric mixer until smooth.
Add sugar, nutmeg and vanilla and continue beating until incorporated.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add milk slowly, beating continuously. Transfer filling to pie shell and smooth top with a spoon.
Bake until pie is set in center and lightly browned.
Takes about 40 minutes in oven on 300°.

title: punch
directions: Combine lemonade, sugar, water, orange juice and pineapple juice in large container.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet.
This recipe will fill an average punch bowl twice.

title: citrus crown cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease generously and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.

title: burnt sugar pie(very good!)
directions: Put a half cup of sugar in skillet and melt until brown, then add boiling water and stir until sugar is all dissolved. Combine 1/2 cup sugar with the flour and egg yolks with a small amount of water.
Add to the burnt mixture.
Cook until thick.
Put in cooked pie shell and frost with two egg whites.
Bake meringue.

title: quick as a wink casserole
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Crumble raw beef over.
Spread catsup and mustard over.
Pour soups over this, onion first.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: heavenly fruit dip
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well. Stir in pineapple juice; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring constantly, until thickens.
Remove from heat. Stir in yogurt.
Let cool; then cover and refrigerate.

title: pecan pralines (candy)
directions: In large kettle, combine first four ingredients.
Cook five minutes over high heat.
Stir while cooking so it does not stick and burn.
Add butter and pecans and cook five minutes more or until it forms soft ball in water.
Remove from heat and beat until creamy.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
If needed, add a little water at end if they get too thick to spoon out.

title: microwave meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into 12 balls and arrange in a circle in 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave at High 9 to 12 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 5 minutes.

title: christmas brunch casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate at least 5 hours or overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: easy and delicious vegetable spanish yellow rice
directions: Cover bottom of heavy pot with enough olive oil to saute onion, green pepper and garlic.
When onion begins to brown, add tomatoes, rice and drained corn.
Stir.
Add liquid according to instructions on rice package.
Bring to boil and cook over high for 1 minute; cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: easy beef tips
directions: In casserole, combine stew meat with remaining ingredients. Cover tightly.
Bake at 300°
for 4 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: easy baking powder biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients together in bowl.
Add oil and milk, mixing with fork until combined.
Put dough on ungreased baking sheet and press flat (or roll) into a rectangle.
Cut into 12 squares.
Spread out and bake for 10 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: chicken curry
directions: Mince garlic, chilies and ginger.
Heat oil in large Dutch oven over medium high heat.
Add onions and saute until brown.
Add 2 tablespoons water during last minutes of cooking to prevent sticking (7 to 10 minutes).
Add garlic mixture and 1 tablespoon water; saute 3 minutes.
Add cinnamon, cardamon and cloves.
Stir 1 minute.
Add 2 tablespoons water, bay leaves, coriander, cumin and turmeric; saute 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and salt.
Cook until almost all liquid evaporates, stirring constantly about 5 minutes. Add chicken pieces 1 at a time; coat in tomato mixture.
Add 1 cup water.
Cover; simmer until chicken is cooked through, turning once, about 40 minutes.
Spoon rice onto plate.
Top with chicken and sauce.
Garnish with cilantro.
Serve with chutney.

title: busy day blueberry crisp
directions: Pour blueberry pie filling into 9-inch square baking pan.
Top with dry cake mix.
Cut butter into very thin slivers and insert into cake mix at intervals.
Bake at 350° until crisp, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry breeze
directions: Step 1:
Cook margarine and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Mix in graham cracker crumbs.
Press evenly and firmly in a 9-inch pie pan to form crust.
Chill.

title: li'l cornbread wraps
directions: Separate dough into 16 strips; cut each strip in half.
Wrap dough around links and press ends together to seal.
Bake as directed on dough package.

title: butter roll
directions: Take an individual biscuit and roll out into cookie shapes, then take a tablespoon of sugar, butter and sprinkle a little cinnamon over the sugar and butter. Take the dough and roll it up and take a fork to seal the end. Place in a glass cooking dish or casserole dish. Do this until all biscuits are rolled. Pour milk over rolls. Spread flavor over rolls. Place in oven at 350°. Bake until bread is brown (15 to 20 minutes).

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat shortening and sugars until creamy. Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt, water and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix together melted butter, onion, mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut ham and cheese into roll size pieces. Spread preceding mixture on rolls.
Add ham slices and cheese squares.
Wrap in foil and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry congealed dish
directions: Mix jello and water, then add all other ingredients except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into long dish and let congeal. Spread sour cream over congealed mixture and add other half of jello mixture and let congeal.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Stir in chopped onion in small bowl.
Beat egg, milk, oil and canned corn together.
Add to dry mixture and mix well.
Lightly grease medium baking dish or iron skillet.
Add 1/2 mixture to baking dish.
Add package of Cheddar cheese to top of mixture and spread out evenly, then add the rest of corn bread mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool, then cut.

title: mushroom oven rice
directions: Saute the rice in butter

for 2 minutes or until golden brown. Add celery and onion; cook and stir for 2 minutes more. Add mushrooms; cook and stir until the celery is tender. Transfer to a greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Separate rolls and place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center of pan. Press to fit bottom of pan and seal seams.
Sprinkle sausage over crust.
Toss together potatoes and cheese and sprinkle over sausage.
Whisk together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Slowly pour over potato layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: magic squares
directions: Melt caramel squares and 1/3 cup milk in double boiler, stirring so it won't stick.
Remove from heat when melted.
Mix cake mix with 1/3 cup milk and margarine, using mixer.
Add nuts.

title: texican tortilla stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown and crumble beef with onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas. Slowly simmer for 1 hour.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a beater.
Put in casserole and top with butter. Refrigerate overnight and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can also be baked immediately.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pay day cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and margarine.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. While cake is hot, top with marshmallows and set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, stir together white syrup, butterscotch chips and vanilla.
Heat on stove until melted.
Add Rice Krispies and salted peanuts.
Spread on top of cake.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Add salt and pepper to ground beef.
Saute until meat juices are absorbed.
Add chopped onion, parsley and 4 tablespoons butter; brown well.
Add tomato sauce and water and simmer until liquid is absorbed, about 15 minutes.
Cook macaroni in salt water 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Rinse and drain well.
Grease large 11 x 14-inch baking pan with melted butter; sprinkle with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Combine macaroni with 1/2 cup melted butter; arrange 1/2 of the mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and cover with meat mixture, spreading evenly over entire surface.
Cover with the remaining macaroni and grated cheese. Prepare Crema.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat.
Add pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Put in the freezer for at least 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate bark.
Dip cold caramel mixture in chocolate bark.
Place on wax paper.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Spread rice in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soups.
Place dry onion soup in a plastic food size bag.
Add chicken pieces and shake.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle on remaining onion soup, if any.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place bacon in a 2-quart microwavable casserole.
Cook, covered with a paper towel, 6 to 6 1/2 minutes at High power or until crisp.
Remove bacon and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Add onions and garlic to drippings.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, uncovered, on High; stir twice.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cook covered 8 to 9 minutes at High power until zucchini is tender; stir twice.
Sprinkle zucchini with Mozzarella cheese; cover and let stand 3 minutes.

title: ritz cookies
directions: Put peanut butter on 1 Ritz and add another Ritz to top.
Use about 2 or 3 packs; this will use all the vanilla coating.
Melt the vanilla in microwave using directions on back.
Coat each cookie and put on cookie sheet or wax paper.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water until thick.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter and garlic cheese until melted.
Mix egg, milk, garlic powder and pepper and add to grits.
Pour into well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with sharp cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: melon boat
directions: Cut out watermelon; seed and cube.
Cut balls from other melons.
Cut and cube pineapple.
Clean grapes and strawberries. Save all juice and combine with grape, lime and lemon juices. Combine all fruits except juices.
Put in melon boat and pour juices over; refrigerate several hours.

title: aunt fay's jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple, mashed bananas and nuts.
Stir well.
Pour half mixture into 13 x 9-inch glass dish and put in icebox until set, about 1 hour.
When set firm, spoon on sour cream and spread over set mixture, then spoon on other half jello mixture and put in icebox until completely set, about 2 hours.
Then serve.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Mix ingredients.
Line a rectangular pan with waxed paper. Spread mix in pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm; roll in confectioners sugar to coat.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add all other ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil potatoes until almost done.
Spray a 9 x 11-inch Pyrex dish with Pam.
Place chicken in bottom of dish.
Top with potatoes and onion.
Mix the soup with water and pour over the potatoes and onion.
Top with dressing mix crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
(Meat loaf is very moist and no grease collects in baking dish.)

title: chicken wild rice salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice and tarragon.
Set aside. In large bowl, combine chicken, wild rice, green onions, water chestnuts, salt and pepper.
Stir in mayonnaise mixture until blended.
Refrigerate covered 2 to 3 hours.
Just before serving, fold in grapes and cashews.
Garnish with grape clusters or sugared strawberries.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: dill bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine in mixing bowl the cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and softened yeast.
Add flour, beating well after each addition.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Stir dough down.
Turn into well greased loaf pan and let rise in warm place 30 to 40 minutes or until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. When done, brush with soft butter and sprinkle with salt.

title: dip
directions: In a bowl, mash Blue cheese with a fork.
Mix cheese with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add onions and pepper and mix well.
Serve dip with bread sticks, assorted crackers or with fresh vegetables. Makes a good party appetizer.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots medium done.
Pour ice water over.
Arrange carrots, peppers and onions in layers.
Mix ingredients, bring to boil and pour over carrots.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: chili dip
directions: Melt cheeses and add chili; stir.
Serve with Fritos.

title: mint and mandarin sauce for lamb
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Steep slowly for 30 minutes.
Serve as sauce for lamb chops or leg of lamb.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all together in blender.
Store in refrigerator.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; must keep fairly firm.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Grease pan. Mix all together until soft. Take heaping tablespoon and roll like a finger. Bake at 350° until lightly brown. While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: breakfast dish(easy dish for a group and can be made the night before.)
directions: Brown meat, drain and place in 9 x 13 pan.
Beat eggs lightly and add rest of ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak 2 cups navy beans overnight in cold water.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Make a layer of asparagus, then a layer of eggs.
Repeat until all are gone.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over asparagus and eggs.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with apples; keep beating until flour is moistened.
Add nuts; place into greased jelly roll pan and spread dough out in pan.

title: quick refreshing salad
directions: Blend all of these ingredients, then add nuts (about 1/4 cup), strawberries (whole or halved) and 1 cup miniature marshmallows. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Beat in egg, then stir in pineapple and dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
These taste like pineapple upside-down cake.

title: low-fat taco salad
directions: Grill chicken breasts, seasoned to taste.
Toss lettuce, tomatoes and onion in large bowl.
Sprinkle cilantro over salad. Cube chicken breasts and lay on top of salad.
Pour 1/2 bag corn chips over, then sprinkle with cheese.
Drizzle with Catalina dressing and serve.
Picante sauce can also be put on top of salad, otherwise, serve with remaining corn chips.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, salt and cornstarch together.
Add beaten eggs, milk, nutmeg and vanilla flavor.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 250°.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Combine margarine, water, cocoa and oil in pan. Bring to a boil and pour over mixture of flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Blend and pour into greased 11 x 16 x 1-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and frost immediately.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add coffee.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Put in glass gallon jar and cool overnight.
Add vodka and vanilla bean, cut into 3 chunks.
Let it sit for 3 weeks shaking it once a day. Yummy!

title: buffalo chips(grandma's no bake cookies)
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in medium saucepan.
Stir and boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Stir.
Quickly drop from tablespoon onto foil or waxed paper greased with margarine.
Let cool.

title: ham noodle casserole
directions: Over low heat, cook mushroom soup diluted with milk, catsup, horseradish and salt.
Add Cheddar cheese and mix with noodles, ham and beans.
Pour into buttered casserole or a 9 x 12-inch cake pan. Cover with buttered whole wheat bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes or until topping is brown and mixture bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, milk, soup, salt, pepper and half the fried onions. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and add remaining onions on top. Cook an additional 5 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.

title: beard's best banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients
and bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Stir in sugar, half of the flour and salt. Beat until smooth. Add egg and shortening.
Beat in the rest of the flour until smooth. Cover with a cloth.
Let rise in warm place until double, approximately 30 minutes. Stir down and spoon dough into 12 large or 20 to 24 regular muffin cups.
Let dough rise to top of muffin cups, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: In bowl, stir together flour and baking soda.
In large mixer bowl, beat margarine with electric mixer on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add carrot, egg whites and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture and beat until well combined.
Stir in oats.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2-inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done, about 10 minutes.
Remove cookies from cookie sheet and cool on wire rack.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: orange juice
directions: Combine ingredients and add enough water to make 5 quarts. Chill and serve.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine to form a crust in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread the remaining ingredients, except milk, in layers on top of crust.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk over layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tropical fruit loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cereal and nuts.
Combine egg, oil, water, pineapple and banana. Add to dry ingredients all at once.
(Mixture will be stiff.) Stir until moistened.
Turn into pan and bake 70 to 75 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.

title: italian beef, spinach and macaroni bake
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. In large kettle or Dutch oven, cook beef, onions, carrots and celery over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Add the tomatoes, salt, garlic powder and oregano. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add macaroni and spinach to beef mixture. Pour into 2 greased 3-quart baking dishes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Yield: 2 casseroles.

title: hominy dish
directions: Mix Cheez Whiz, chili powder, soup and onion.
Heat and pour over hominy.
Pour hominy mix into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle potato chips on top and bake at 350° for minutes.
Last few minutes of baking time, sprinkle cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into iron skillet.
Cover the top with more ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain peas and beans; chop the eggs.
The eggs, peas, beans, celery, onion, pickles, cheese and ham can be mixed a little.
Add the drained macaroni.
Mix together the sandwich spread, salt, pepper, sugar and milk well.
Add to the rest.

title: fish chowder
directions: Saute leeks, potatoes and carrots in the butter in a soup kettle for 5 minutes, until tender but not brown.
Cut the fish into bite-size pieces and place into the kettle.
Add the water and salt and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add the celery soup, cucumber and milk.
Heat just to boiling and serve.
Serves 6.

title: chicken-n-macaroni gumbo
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Dice into chunks.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine chicken chunks, macaroni and broccoli into large pot.
Stir in carrots and cream of chicken soup.
Top these ingredients with shredded cheese.

title: new orleans dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, dill weed, seasoned salt and green onion. Let stand in the refrigerator at least 6 hours. It is best made a day ahead. Serve with any fresh vegetables.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter an 8-inch square cake pan.
Mix the 1 cup sugar, the flour and the baking powder in a large bowl. Work in butter with your fingers or a pastry blender until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add the egg and milk; blend.
Spoon into a cake pan.
Sprinkle the sugar-cinnamon mixture evenly over the top.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Wash and hull strawberries; chop or crush.
Add sugar and let stand several hours.
Combine with all other ingredients. Freeze until firm (in ice cream freezer).

title: blintz casserole
directions: Combine sour cream, eggs, sugar, margarine and vanilla until smooth.
Grease casserole (square pan 9 x 9-inch).
Place blintzs in pan.
Pour mixture over blintzs.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until set.
Serve warm and enjoy.
Perfect for brunch. Serves 6 to 8.

title: greens quesadilla
directions: Place 1/2 cup ingredients on each shell.
Fold in half and fry until golden brown on each side. Slice boiled egg and place on top of quesadilla and top with ranch dressing. (Or your favorite dressing.)

title: chili powder
directions: Place all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Toss gently with spoon until well blended.
Store in airtight container in cool, dark, dry place for up to 6 months.
Use in place of packaged chili powder.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Dip chicken in melted butter and lay on top of rice.
Mix water, cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: homemade crock-pot spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper in medium pan.
Pour off fat.
Pour meat into crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Cook in crock-pot on low.
Heat all day (about 6 to 8 hours) or on high about 3 hours.
During last 30 minutes to 1 hour, add cheeses and stir well.
Serve over spaghetti noodles or ravioli (if sauce is too thick, add a can of water).

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, spice, soda, raisins, water, vanilla and oats to flour.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° until done.

title: karo classic pecan pie
directions: Stir together all ingredients (except pecans) until blended. Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.

title: quick casserole
directions: Put raw ground chuck in the bottom of a large baking dish. Arrange a layer of sliced potatoes on top of meat, then a layer of carrots.
Top with layer of potatoes.
Pour soup mixed with milk over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grate pepper, onion and cheese.
Mix meal, sugar, eggs and oil.
Add milk, corn and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Roll each quartered apple in a crescent roll.
Place in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and butter in saucepan; melt until it boils, stirring occasionally.
Spread over dumplings.
Pour Mountain Dew over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in water with salt and pepper to taste.
When tender, drain water and add milk, cheese, onion soup and rice. Bake in oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: egg roll
directions: Brush egg wrapper with egg yolk.
Fill with vegetable mixture. Bake or fry.

title: walking taco
directions: Place in casserole dish as listed.
The reason it is called a Walking Taco, is because it is the kind of dip you bring to a pot luck cocktail party.
It is usually enjoyed by everyone.
This is a California favorite.

title: coke salad
directions: Use the reserved syrup from black cherries and pineapple to the preparation of jello.
Add cream cheese to the hot jello mixture. When cool, add Coke.
Mix cherries, pineapple and nuts in jello mixture and chill.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift in cocoa, flour and salt.
Mix vinegar with milk.
Add soda.
As mixture rises, add to mixture.
Add boiling water and vanilla.
Mix.
Pour into greased and floured 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator.

title: hot fudge ice cream bars
directions: Pour chocolate syrup into medium microwavable-safe bowl and microwave for 2 minutes on High (do not boil). Stir peanut butter into hot chocolate with a whisk until smooth. Allow to cool to room temperature. Line the bottom of a 9 x 13 dish with 9 1/2 ice cream sandwiches. Spread half the whipped topping over the sandwiches. Spoon half the chocolate mixture over whipped topping. Top with half the peanuts. Repeat layers. Freeze until firm, about 1 hour. Cut into squares to serve. Yield: 15 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter and pour over sugar.
Add beaten eggs to sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in Pet-Ritz pie shell until done at 350°.

title: pepperoni squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles. Press perforations to seal.
Cut each rectangle into 4 strips. Combine pepperoni, onion, mustard and poppy seed in bowl and mix well.
Place about 1 teaspoon of pepperoni mixture on one-half of each dough strip.
Fold the other half of strip over to cover the pepperoni mixture.
Using the tongs of a fork, press the 3 sides of the square to seal.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 18 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: tuno-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Add ingredients; let chill.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in oblong pan about (10 x 15-inches), then spread cracker crumbs evenly over butter.
Add other ingredients in layers with milk on top (do not stir).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, sugar and salt into bowl.
Mix thoroughly with fork the shortening, egg yolk, milk and vanilla. Form into balls size of walnut.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Press 1/16-inch thick with bottom of greased glass dipped in sugar. Brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: john mazetti
directions: Brown meat with onion. Combine with tomatoes and juice. Cook until it boils. Add mushroom soup and cook 10 minutes. Add noodles and cook for 15 minutes. Add cheese and cook slowly for 15 minutes. Add salt and pepper. Serve hot.

title: apple kraut salad
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar in small pan.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables and apple.
Toss.
Let stand overnight.

title: betty's spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and margarine; drain off grease.
Add cooked rice and tomatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheddar-spinach pie
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings. Add cheese mixture and spinach; mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix.
Simmer on low for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: old fashion pecan pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add other ingredients and blend. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Garnish with half pecan pieces. Cook in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine butter, sugar and potatoes; also, add salt, potato water and milk.
When cool, add eggs and yeast.
Add flour to make dough stiff.
Knead thoroughly.
Let rise 1 hour.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with brown sugar, raisins, nuts, cinnamon or whatever desired. Bake at 375° until done.

title: cookie press cookies
directions: Cream the shortening. Add sugar. Add well beaten egg.
Mix and sift dry ingredients. Add to first mixture. Add vanilla.
Put dough in cookie press.
Bake on ungreased pan at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: viennese dessert bars
directions: Mix butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and blend well.
Add flour gradually and then stir in nuts.
Spoon half of batter into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with jam; cover with remaining batter.
Spread with spatula dipped in hot water and then wiped.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool and then cut into bars.

title: slumgullion
directions: Fry the meat and onions until done.
Mix all together.
Cook until done.
Salt to taste.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Cut muffin in half. Spoon tomato sauce on each half.
sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 3 Min.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix the egg, sugar, butter and nutmeats together and cook over slow heat until it boils up.
Remove from heat. Add the cereal. Shape into balls and roll in coconut.
Yields 5 1/2 dozen.

title: impossible chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and morsels.
Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes for chewy cookies or 9 to 10 minutes for crispy cookies.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, onion, green chilies and 1 1/2 cups cheese. In a separate bowl, mix soup and sour cream. Stir 1/2 cup of soup/cream sauce into chicken mixture. Fill tortillas with 1/4 cup mixture and roll. Place enchiladas in baking dish. Top with remaining sauce and cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 5.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Season and boil chicken.
Cook noodles as stated on package. Cut chicken into pieces.
Mix noodles and chicken, then add soup and gravy.
Pour mixture into pan; sprinkle layer of cheese. Cover with rolls.
Cook until rolls are brown.

title: crystal pickles
directions: For 4 mornings drain & heat syrup then pour over pickles. Fifth morning, pack pickles in jars, heat syrup, and pour over pickles and seal.

title: coconut blender pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a deep 9 1/2-inch Pie Pan. Sprinkle Coconut in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients in a Blender for 30 to 60 seconds on high.
Pour over Coconut.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until golden brown and knife comes out of center clean.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In a large
skillet, mix the first 6 ingredients.
Stir over low heat
until
chocolate melts.
Then over medium heat, continue stirring until
it	reaches
a
rolling boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Take off heat;
add
vanilla
and nuts.
Let cool to lukewarm. Beat until thick and pour in buttered pan.

title: beef pepper steak
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add meat and brown.
Remove meat to dish.
Add onion, garlic pieces and green pepper slices to skillet and cook until just tender.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and soy sauce.
Add sugar, garlic salt and pepper.
Pour this into skillet over vegetables, stirring until sauce is thickened and clear.
Add cooked meat, cook about 5 to 10 minutes longer and serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mushroom bread
directions: Mix first four ingredients together; let set until bubbling, then in a large bowl, put Pet milk, oil, sugar and salt.
Add this to yeast mixture and mix with mixer.
Then add flour, one cup at a time.
Fold with a wooden spoon.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Stir in vanilla and rum extract.
Stir in flour, nutmeg, cherries and nuts.
Chill dough. Shape dough into rolls 1 inch in diameter.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.
(Dough may be frozen at this stage and held until needed.)
Slice cookies 1/4 inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes or until edges are golden.
Makes 14 dozen cookies.

title: fiesta corn
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, mix eggs and cornmeal.
Add corn, milk, margarine, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Pour 1/2 the corn mixture into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese and chiles.
Add remaining corn mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in 3-quart saucepan. Add onion; cook, stirring often, 2 minutes or until tender. Whisk in soup, milk, hot sauce and half of cheese, stirring just until cheese melts. Stir in macaroni; pour into a lightly greased 9-inch square baking dish. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: chocolate peanut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg yolk with fork in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Stir in baking mix, nuts and chips.

title: cheese ball(double for larger amounts)
directions: Mix well.
Make into a ball. Roll in chopped nuts and dried beef, chopped.
Cool and let set awhile.

title: brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs; add sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir together flour, cocoa and salt; add to butter mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Add walnuts; pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes or until set; cool. Serve with whipped cream.
Delicious with ice cream also.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bits of beef
directions: Mix in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: love bread
directions: Stand biscuits on their side in Bundt pan.
Pour melted butter over top and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: swedish spritz
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, sugar, egg yolks and flavoring thoroughly.
Measure flour and work into mix slowly.
Force dough through cookie press onto ungreased baking sheet in desired shapes.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until set, but not brown.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350° with rack in center position.
Roll chilled dough into walnut size balls and place 2-inches apart.
Bake until the tops are dry 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: pine tarts
directions: Cook pineapple in juice with sugar until thickened on a slow fire; set aside to cool.
Sift flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut shortening in with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture is in pieces about the size of peas.
Add ice water a little at a time and toss mixture with a fork until flour is dampened.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Roll out dough; cut pieces into squares.
Place pineapple mixture in center (about a tablespoon).
Fold ends to form triangle.
Brush with melted margarine or beaten egg yolk and bake for 1/2 to 3/4 hour at 350° in preheated oven.

title: saucepan fudgies
directions: In large heavy saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Put on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool, then eat.
Awe so good!

title: foil wrapped steak
directions: Tear off enough foil to completely cover meat and vegetables. Place meat in center of foil on cookie sheet.
Spread onion soup mix on top.
Place chunks of pared carrots and potatoes on meat. Dot with butter.
Seal foil around entire thing to hold in meat juices.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until vegetables are soft. The meat juices may be used to make a delicious gravy.
Serves 4.

title: 3 step lasagne
directions: Step 1:
Cook beef, pork, onion and garlic in large sauce pan. Drain off all fat.
Add tomatoes, and break them up with a fork. Stir in tomato sauce, 2 Tbsp. parsley flakes, sugar, 1 tsp. salt and basil.
Heat to boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered for 1 hour or until mixture is the consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Reserve at least 1/2 cup of meat sauce mixture for finally topping.

title: camp potatoes
directions: Scrub and peel as many potatoes as you wish to serve (one per person). Melt oleo or shortening or pour oil in skillet.
Chop up onion and brown a bit.
Slice potatoes and brown them a bit. Cover with water, salt and pepper.
Cover skillet with lid and simmer; stirring occasionally.
Great for camping; a good compliment to those fish you caught.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Place softened cream cheese in medium mixing bowl.
Chop green onions (use whole onion, green and all).
Cut dried beef into small pieces and add broth to cream cheese.
Add Accent and mix all well.
Roll into ball and ground pecans or walnuts (nuts are optional).
Keep chilled until serving time.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix and pat in pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 400° 15 minutes or until brown.

title: orange-sesame braised shark
directions: In a small pie plate, mix sesame seed with cornstarch and cayenne pepper.
Dredge shark steaks in this mixture.
Set steaks aside and reserve 1 tablespoon of sesame-cornstarch mixture.
Heat the oil over medium-high heat in a large non-stick skillet.
Brown the steaks in the hot oil on both sides.
Remove from pan and reserve.
Add the onion to the oil in the pan, lower heat to medium-low and cook until onion browns lightly, about 5 minutes. Add ginger and garlic; cook another minute.
Add orange juice and soy sauce.
Heat to a simmer.
Return the shark steaks to the pan, cover and simmer for 8 minutes.
While shark is cooking, mix 1 tablespoon of remaining sesame-cornstarch mixture with the water. When shark is cooked, remove to a warm plate and heat the sauce in the pan to a boil.
Stir in the cornstarch mixture and stir until sauce thickens, about 10 seconds.
Remove from heat, stir in sherry, sesame oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over fish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy oven beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.

title: ham, cheese and raisin sticks
directions: Melt
butter
in
a
9	x
13-inch
pan.
Stir remaining ingredients together to make a soft dough.	Gently smooth dough into a ball on
a
floured surface.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into a rectangle, 10
x 6-inches.
Cut lengthwise in half;	cut each half into 12
sticks,	about
3/4 inch wide.
Roll each in butter in pan.
Bake in
a 425° oven for 15 minutes. Serve hot. Yield:
24 sticks.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Mix all together until it looks like large peas.
Put in a tight sealed container and store.

title: banana pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl combine Eagle Brand and water.
Add pudding mix, beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mix into 2 1/2-quart round glass bowl.
Top with wafers and bananas.
End with pudding mix. Chill thoroughly. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Will need 4 toothpicks.

title: turkey lasagne(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix noodles, soup, milk and poultry seasoning.
Mix cream cheese and cottage cheese.
Heat; add olives, onion, green pepper and parsley.
In a 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking pan layer noodles, cheese, turkey and sauce.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: our favorite wings
directions: Deep fry wings at 400° for 12 minutes or bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Turn halfway.

title: gazpacho
directions: Add onion soup or onion and parsley to juice; stir.
Mix seasonings together; add and stir well.
Mix liquids together; add and stir well.
Add cucumbers, tomatoes and red pepper.
Stir and chill at least 4 hours or best overnight.
Serves 8.
Will keep several days.

title: microwave chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of microwavable pan.
Pour chili over cheese, then sprinkle cheese mixture over chili.
Microwave for 7 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter; stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Pack crumb mixture evenly in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer in order as listed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese apples
directions: Cream butter, sugar, flour and cheese.
Place apples in buttered dish.
Put cheese mixture over apples.
Make holes in mixture.
Pour in milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber freezer pickles
directions: Mix together and let soak for 2 hours at room temperature. Drain well.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar and add to cucumbers.
Put in containers and freeze for 4 days!

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Boil water and add orange jello.
Dissolve.
Add cup of cold juice.
Refrigerate until it begins to thicken.
Then add oranges, bananas and cottage cheese.

title: friendship bread
directions: To make the bread:
Combine 1 cup of starter, oil, eggs and vanilla in a bowl; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into starter mixture just until combined.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon into two well greased 9 x 4 x 2-inch baking pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until breads test done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: zucchini bread and glaze
directions: Combine vegetable oil, eggs, sugar and flour.
Mix well and then add zucchini, vanilla, cinnamon and walnuts.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: garlic and lentil soup
directions: Soak lentils or beans overnight.
Wash lentils or beans and throw out any bad ones.
Cover lentils in about 2 1/2 quarts of water, add bouillon cubes and bring to a boil and
simmer until they are tender.
Saute celery, onion, and garlic.
Add sauteed mixture and bay leaves to lentils and simmer until all ingredients are tender.
Add lemon pepper seasoning to taste.
You can also add other seasoning.

title: potato souffle
directions: Beat hot milk, cheese, butter and seasonings into hot, mashed potatoes.
Beat egg yolks until thin and lemon-colored and add to potato mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into potato mixture.
Put into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Spread sugar in pan and cover with enough water to dissolve sugar, stirring constantly. Add paraffin. Continue to stir and cook until mixture ropes from spoon.
Add peanuts and cook until peanuts are parched (peanuts will crack or pop when starting to parch).
Remove from fire and stir in soda (makes mixture foam). Quickly spread mixture very thin on greased pan.
Keep mixture loosened from pan with spatula until it is cold.
When cold, break candy into small pieces. This makes a large quantity.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine ground beef and onion in skillet; cook until meat is lightly brown.
Drain; add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese. Place biscuits on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour together.
Separate egg yolks and whites (reserved for top).
Mix 1 cup milk and 3 egg yolks together.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Add rest of milk.
Cook on top of stove in a good heavy saucepan, stirring constantly so it won't stick or scorch.
When gets thick, remove from stove.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into 9 1/2-inch cooked pie crust.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar gradually while beating for 1 minute longer.
Spread on top of pie and sprinkle coconut on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/2-inch shell.
Parboil shells 5 minutes; drain.
Reserve.
Chop the pulp and saute chopped eggplant, mushrooms and onions in butter or margarine over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix in salt, pepper and shrimp.
Pile into eggplant shells.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake in 375° oven 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry or peach pie
directions: Double ingredients for 2 pies.

title: mary ann's chili
directions: Brown beef or turkey; drain fat.
Stir in Seasoning, tomato sauce or whole tomatoes and kidney beans.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy broccoli pockets
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 baking sheets.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well.

title: barley-lentil soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot, except for spinach or green beans.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, for 50 minutes, or until lentils and barley are tender.
Add spinach or green beans; cook for another 10 minutes.
More water can be added if the consistency is too thick.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and place in refrigerator. Knead every day for 4 days.
Shape into loaves.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 150° for 9 hours.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt 1 1/2 pounds of white bark in oven at the lowest temperature.
Remove from oven and add 1 cup of peanut butter. Add 2 cups of dry salted peanuts, also 2 cups of mini marshmallows and 3 cups of Rice Krispies.
Mix and put into a 9 x 12-inch pan. When set, cut in small squares.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Chop in large bowl the lettuce, broccoli, cauliflower, radishes, green peppers, onions, frozen peas and Cheddar cheese. Sprinkle top of cheese with garlic powder.
Cover top of bowl with mayo.
Cover bowl and let set overnight or all day in refrigerator.
Before serving, toss.

title: corn casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: elderberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then lower heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coffee can pumpkin cake
directions: You will also need 4 coffee cans.

title: hot corn
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan over low heat.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Combine cheese mixture with remaining ingredients in 2-quart baking dish.
Add jalapeno peppers, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: party mushroom sandwiches
directions: In a saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter. Add and blend in flour. Slowly stir in hot milk that has dissolved bouillon cube in it. Add seasonings and Tabasco. Wash mushrooms and dry on paper towels. Saute mushrooms in 2

tablespoons butter over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes. Cool. Chop mushrooms and add to hot cream sauce. Allow mixture to cool. Spread on bread slices, roll and secure with a toothpick. Brush rolls with remaining 1 tablespoon melted butter; refrigerate. Place on greased cookie sheet when ready to serve and toast at 350° for about 20 minutes or until nicely browned. May be completely prepared baked and frozen; just reheat to serve.

title: frosty cherry dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine pineapple, pie filling and milk; fold in the whipped topping. Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Cover and freeze until firm. Garnish with cherries and whipped topping, if desired. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: green beans
directions: Fry bacon; set aside to cool.
In bacon grease, mix vinegar, sugar and water.
Add flour to thicken.
Crumble bacon and add to beans and mushrooms.
Pour sauce over bean mixture.
Add onion rings for topping.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients together (sprinkle jello in dry). Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Cook chicken. Remove skin and bones. Cook broccoli; drain well.

Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, grated cheese, lemon juice and seasonings. Arrange broccoli in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese. Spread pieces of chicken over broccoli.
Sprinkle again with Parmesan cheese. Pour sauce over all. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese generously again and with paprika. Dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Bake pie
shell
and cool it.
In small pan, mix sugar, cornstarch	and
water.
Cook
until
thick and clear.
Remove from heat
and
stir
in lemon or peach jello until dissolved. Let this
cool.
Slice fresh peaches and fill pie crust.
Pour the cooled
filling
over the peaches and refrigerate.	Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: bacon poles(yield: 20 servings)
directions: Cut bacon into halves lengthwise.
Wrap bacon barber pole fashion around breadsticks.

title: broiled hamburger t-bones
directions: Shape meat in form of a t-bone and spread shortening over meat. Broil 7 minutes. Turn. Cover other side with shortening and broil 7 minutes more.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the vegetables as listed.
Spread mayonnaise over the layers.
Top with bacon bits and cheese.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and drain.
In same pot, add butter and begin to mash potatoes with an electric mixer.

Add remaining ingredients, except for 1/4 cup of cheese, and continue to beat until smooth. Turn into a greased casserole, top with remaining cheese, cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Add olive oil, vinegar, mustard and horseradish to mayonnaise. Mix thoroughly.
Slowly add tomato catsup until mixture is consistency of mayonnaise before ingredients were added.
Stir in chopped vegetables and salt and hot pepper sauce.
Serve over boiled shrimp or crabs, raw oysters and also over wedges of iceberg lettuce.

title: popeye biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients except for butter.
Roll out and form into biscuits shape.
Dip in butter.
Bake at 425 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken in water and skim off the
foam. Add boullion cubes.
When chicken is cooked, remove, cool and shred meat. Brown pine nuts in butter till golden brown.
Remove nuts and then brown onions.
Wash rice and put into broth.
Cover and let rice cook. When rice is nearly done, add chicken, onions, pine nuts and seasoning.

title: creamed chicken over biscuits
directions: Blend in milk until soupy. Cook until warm. Serve over biscuits. Can add vegetables, if you desire.

title: granny's ham dumplings
directions: Boil ham in water until very tender.
Remove from broth.
Add enough water to make 2 quarts and bring to a boil.
Add dumplings. Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Add diced ham, eggs, salt and pepper. Warms you up on a cold night.

title: milnot party dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling pineapple juice.
Add lemon juice and set aside until partly set.

title: trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
6 qts.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Butter a large cookie sheet.
Cook the first 4 ingredients at high temperature until boiling.
Add peanuts.
Boil until syrup begins to turn brown (about 7 minutes).
Add soda; stir only until soda dissolves.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Do not spread. Allow brittle to spread by itself.
After it cools, break into small pieces.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Boil coffee, water and sugar 20 minutes.
Cool.
Add vanilla and vodka.

title: peanut butter log cookies
directions: In a bowl, mix together the peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar.
Add the Cocoa Krispies.
Press into little logs.
Roll into ground nuts. Drizzle chocolate over the top.
Let set until chocolate is firm.

title: chocolate muffins
directions: Mix sugar and flour
and add eggs one at a time.
In microwave, melt margarine and semi-sweet chocolate.
Blend into sugar and flour mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake in silver muffin cups in muffin pans 25 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: chicken-cordon bleu
directions: Place meat between sheets of plastic wrap.
With the flat side of a wooden mallet, pound out to a 5 or 6-inch diameter.
Place 1 slice each of ham and cheese on the bottom half of each piece of chicken.
Fold (or roll) completely enveloping filling.
Press edges together to seal.
Again cover with a plastic wrap and pound with your hands to remove air bubbles.
Sprinkle cornstarch over a piece of plastic wrap and lightly cover meat on both sides.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender, 1 to 2 hours.

title: chicken vegetable skillet
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken; drain.
Add peas and carrots, soup mix and parsley blended with water. Simmer, covered, 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: crunchy broccoli salad
directions: Rinse broccoli in several changes of cool water. Trim hard fiber parts and discard. Chop stems and florets into bite-sized pieces. Set aside. Make dressing by combining salad dressing, vinegar, sugar, onion and raisins. Refrigerate overnight, if possible. At serving, drizzle dressing over broccoli and add sunflower seeds and bacon bits. Toss lightly and serve immediately. Chicken may be added for a heartier salad.

title: sloppy joes(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet.
Pour into colander and rinse well.
Put into crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (high 3 to 4 hours).

title: mexican dip
directions: Line a pie plate with cream cheese.
Dice pepper and onion and sprinkle over cream cheese.
Pour salsa over all of it.
Blend the Longhorn cheese in blender and put over mixture.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cover pan with foil as soon as taken from oven to keep moist.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Prepare and bake corn bread mix according to package directions.
Cool, then crumble into large mixing bowl.
Add the chopped vegetables.
Add Miracle Whip and mustard.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: hermits
directions: Mix together all but one egg.
Put dough on cookie sheet in long strip; brush with beaten egg.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°. Yummy.

title: rit pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine and walnuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, greased with margarine.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: hasenbraten
directions: Cut rabbit into serving size pieces and cook in salted water until tender.
Place in a baking pan.
Mix sour cream, flour, salt, a dash of white pepper and garlic powder.
Pour this over rabbit.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together frozen hash browns, soup, cream cheese, sour cream and onion.
Grease lasagna size pan and put mixture in pan. Top with Cheddar cheese, then stuffing.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese hamburg
directions: Fry onions and hamburg.
Add celery, soup and green pepper. Simmer 1 hour.
Add mushrooms.
Serve over noodles.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Brown bacon crispy; set aside.
Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in bacon grease.
Drain after sauteed.
Add Ro-Tel and stewed tomatoes and sausage to mixture.
Cook on medium heat 45 minutes.
Turn heat down; add cooked rice and stir thoroughly.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix egg whites, salt and water.
Beat until stiff Stir in pecans and mix well.
Put in sugar and cinnamon and mix well.
Put in greased pan. Cook for about 10 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on foil and let cool.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool, put on cake server or plate.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Spread a small amount of whipped cream on cake.
Spread full can of pie filling on cake.
Dot with whipped cream.
Refrigerate cake.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix and freeze in muffin cups. Remove from freezer as needed.

title: chicken scarperello
directions: Saute sausage in olive oil until golden.
Drain off excess oil and add sliced bell pepper and onion.
Cook 10 minutes on medium heat.
Add chicken and white wine.
Cook on high until done, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 2 to 4 people. Serve alone or over rice or pasta.

title: heavenly hash fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix together. Add marshmallows.
Beat Dream Whip according to package.
Mix salad dressing and cream cheese together and add to fruit.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Place cherries and nuts on top.
Chill before serving.

title: jam tarts
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and butter, beating until well blended.
Stir in flour and salt, mixing well.
Form into a ball.
Cover and chill for 30 minutes.
Using about 1 tablespoon dough, press into a 2 1/2-inch tart pan.
Keep dough as even in thickness as possible.
Trim or shape top evenly.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon preserves into each tart shell.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden crust.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oleo together.
Press into bottom of the pan.
Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and sugar together.
Spread over cake mixture in the pan.
Sprinkle chopped pecans over the top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cut when cool.
Makes 48 (1-inch) square bars.

title: mary's double crust chicken pot pie
directions: *Or 1 can mixed vegetables, drained.

title: health muffins
directions: Pour the orange juice and rind over the 3 kinds of cereal. Pour 1 cup of boiling water over this.
Do not stir.
Let stand until lukewarm.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream milk, butter and sugar together.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: meal pies
directions: Mix sugar and meal.
Add milk.
Add butter, eggs and vanilla and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° until done in center.

title: blueberry pecan crumb coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and oil with sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to butter mixture.
Add sour cream alternately with flour mixture until mixed.
Fold in lemon rind and blueberries.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fire ant control
directions: Mix these four together by shaking in a quart jar and then add to this, 5 pounds white cornmeal.
Mix well!
The mixture should be barely damp.
Sprinkle 1 to 2 tablespoons of mixture on top of each mound.
Must be used within 3 weeks.
Keep in tightly covered container.
You may want to cut the recipe in half.

title: butter bits
directions: Cream the margarine.
Slowly stir in sugar, beating well. Beat in egg yolks one at a time.
Stir in flavoring and flour. Working with wooden spoon, work to make smooth dough balls (1/2-inch balls) and place 2 inches apart on ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: upside-down ham loaf
directions: Melt butter in greased loaf pan or casserole.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Stud pineapple with cloves and arrange over the sugar.
Combine ham and remaining ingredients.
Pack into pan or casserole on top of pineapple wedges.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn out upside-down on a hot platter.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no-yolk caesar salad dressing
directions: Mash anchovies to a paste.
Whisk in garlic, lemon juice and mustard until combined.
Whisk in vinegar.

title: ham-macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake in a preheated oven (350°) until cheese is melted.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix sugar, salt and spices in bowl.
Spread 1/4 of this mixture into shallow 10 x 15-inch baking dish.
Dip pecans into egg and butter mixture and then into spice mixture.
Place into pan; sprinkle rest of spice mixture over nuts in pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 300° or until nuts are light brown.
Stir to separate.
Cool and store in tightly closed container.

title: carrot and raisin salad *
directions: Stir the carrots, raisins and walnuts together.
Beat the orange juice, mayonnaise, yogurt, orange rind and sugar together with whisk or fork.
Toss with the carrot mixture.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Section #1:
Melt butter, vegetable oil and cocoa.
Allow mixture to cool.

title: prune-pecan bread(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan with vegetable spray.
Set aside.
In saucepan, mix prune puree or butter, juice and peel.
Bring just to boiling.
Remove from heat; set aside.
In large bowl, combine wheat germ, flours, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir to blend thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Spread batter in prepared pan.
Bake about 50 minutes until pick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack to cool completely.
Makes 24 slices.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch; add egg and liquids.
Cook to thickness wanted.
Add crisp bacon and fat.
Use on Spinach Salad.

title: chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle garlic salt around the meat and place in baking dish. Place carrots and potatoes around.
Combine ingredients and pour over roast.
Cover with heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cook halved green peppers in boiling water for 2 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Oil a shallow baking dish.

Cook onion until soft, add meat and cook lightly for 5 to 10 minutes. Add tomatoes, parsley, basil, salt and pepper, combining thoroughly. Lightly fill each pepper half with mixture and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Simmer celery, green peppers and onions in drippings until done.
Add peas, tomatoes and chopped bacon.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: quick stew
directions: Brown beef
in	Dutch
oven.
Add other ingredients and cook for 30 minutes covered at medium heat (350° to 375°).

title: mama's christmas ham
directions: Mix first four ingredients; blend in cornstarch.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in brandy flavoring.
Let cool.

title: my favorite potato salad
directions: Put first 9 ingredients in a large bowl; add mustard to mayonnaise, then add to ingredients in bowl.
Mix until all ingredients are coated with mayonnaise mixture.
Serves 8.

title: pickled okra
directions: Bring salt, water and vinegar to boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over okra and other ingredients in jars and seal. Put in bottom of each jar:
1/2 teaspoon celery seed, 1 teaspoon dill seed, 1 clove garlic and 1 small hot pepper pod (I use jalapeno and split up the sides halfway).
Makes 5 pints.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Season and cook chicken in enough water to have 1 1/2 quarts broth.
Chop and saute onions and peppers in oleo.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add Ro-Tel, onions and peppers and cook until mixed well.
Add peas and mushrooms, then cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add deboned chicken and cook in casserole until it bubbles.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together. Put in crust of your choice. Refrigerate. After slicing, top pie with Cool Whip and drizzle chocolate syrup over the top.

title: ducha punza(spanish for shower punch)
directions: Mix together and serve chilled with ice.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add cream of tartar.
Continue beating until stiff.
