Add vanilla, sugar, nuts and crackers.
Pour into a large greased pie plate and spread evenly.
Cook on top shelf of oven at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes (until lightly brown).
Cool completely before filling.

title: sweet potato-apple casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish, layer sweet potatoes, sugar, apple pie filling, orange juice and cinnamon.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.
You may sprinkle miniature marshmallows on top.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in cupcake liners in muffin pan.
Take out of freezer approximately 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed.
Add well beaten egg to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients and blend. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts, just to blended stage.
Drop 3-inches apart by tablespoon on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on sheet, then remove.

title: creamy chicken and dumplings
directions: In Dutch oven or large heavy saucepan, combine water, chicken, onion, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and cool. Bone chicken. Return meat to broth. Bring to a boil. Drop about 1/4 of the tortilla strips into the boiling broth to cover surface. Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Repeat until all strips are added. Remove from heat.
Blend in flour and sour cream. Slowly stir into broth and heat through, stirring constantly. Garnish with chopped parsley or paprika.

title: squash balls
directions: Cook squash and onion in a small amount of water.
Drain well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix other ingredients and roll into small balls.
Fry in deep oil.

title: orange slice squares
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in eggs, mixing well. Add flour, candied orange slices and pecans. Stir until blended.
Spread batter into a well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Cool completely in pan. Remove from pan and sprinkle all sides with powdered sugar. Yields about 3 dozen.

title: vegetable soup 1
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.Put into hot sterilized jars and seal or put into freezer containers.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all together in blender just long enough to blend.
Good with raw vegetables.

title: potato-topped beef casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in casserole in order listed.
Pour 1 cup water over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, for several minutes longer, or until potatoes are brown.

title: cold yogurt-cucumber soup
directions: Chop cucumbers and garlic.
Puree everything in blender, except scallions.
Chill in refrigerator.
Top with scallions. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: honey glazed onions
directions: Cook onions in boiling salted water over low heat for 15 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Drain and place in a shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over onions. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, basting frequently.
Yields 12 servings.

title: best ever oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and flavor, and beat well.
Add
rolled oats.
Let stand while you sift flour with baking soda.
Add to oats mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased
cookie
sheet. Bake in moderate oven (350°) until lightly browned.
Very old recipe.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients and pour in crust.
Chill for 1 hour before you serve.

title: peppermint ice cream dessert
directions: Butter and grease 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Prepare graham cracker crust mixture of choice and cover bottom of dish, reserving a few crumbs for topping.
Soften butter or oleo.
Add powdered sugar, melted chocolate and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites and fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour over crust and freeze.
Cover with ice cream of choice.
Vanilla is good and so is mint chocolate chip.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: raspberry slush
directions: Mix all together and freeze until ready to use.
Serve partially frozen.

title: super easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat; stir in peanut butter, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in confectioners sugar until blended.
Place in lightly greased 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut into 1-inch squares to serve.

title: mock strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except milk).
Heat and then cool. Beat the milk with mixer until stiff.
Fold into Jell-O mixture. Pour into graham cracker pie shell.
Chill and serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: fellowship club chili
directions: Brown meat.
Cut onions and celery and steam until soft.
Put all ingredients into Nesco and let get to boil 15 minutes.
Then let simmer 3 hours and serve with noodles, cheese and crackers.

title: three men in a boat
directions: Bake the potato; cut in half.
Scoop out some of the inside so that it looks like a boat.
Replace the scooped out section with cooked ground meat mixed with sour cream.
Cut a sail from slice of cheese and stand upright in the boat on a toothpick.
Place 3 mushrooms on the edge of the potato "boat" for the 3 "men."

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef; stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
This will be thick.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin pan, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of the mixture (meat) into biscuit lined cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shred cheese; set aside.
In 2 quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour; add milk all at once; cook stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking and stirring until cheese melts. Remove from heat.
Spread 1/2 cheese sauce in bottom of shallow 2 1/2 quart baking dish.
Slice potatoes and onions.
Arrange potato and onion slices over cheese sauce layer.
Top with remaining cheese sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until potatoes are done. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bring apricot juice and brown sugar to a boil; add the pecans and apricots.
Pour over sweet potatoes that have been drained and put into casserole.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.

title: croutons with three cheeses and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Arrange bread on baking sheet.
Brush with olive oil.
Bake until croutons are golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Set aside.
Increase oven to 350°.

title: best beef dip
directions: Wash each
slice of dried beef to remove salt.	Chop in half and
slice thinly.	Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Combine beef and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: bonnie's potato chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla. Add chips, soda and flour. Blend well. Roll dough into balls and flatten onto ungreased cookie sheet with a fork. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Refrigerate dough until ready to place on cookie sheet.

title: low-fat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with vegetables, chips or anything of your choice.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix as for cake.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Floured raisins may be added, if desired.
Omit ginger for molasses cake.
Serve with hot lemon sauce.

title: dutch babies
directions: Preheat oven
Put butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan and melt
in
oven.
Whip eggs on high in blender.
Slowly add milk, then
flour.
Beat for 30 seconds.
Pour batter over hot butter. Bake
to
minutes.
When
done, sprinkle with powdered sugar, then squeeze lemon juice over the top.
Cut in squares and add fresh or frozen fruit.
A wonderful brunch for company.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Mix together and, in an oblong dish, start a layer of cookies, then bananas, then pudding, ending with pudding as top layer.
Crumble cookies on top.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in small amount of water; set aside.
Heat butter in pan.
Add flour; cook until bubbly.
Add 3 cups water; stir until well blended.
Add remaining water with dissolved bouillon and cheese.
Add vegetables undrained.
Heat and serve.

title: turkey hash
directions: Brown butter and ground turkey.
Stir in onion and hash browns. Cook until onion is partially cooked.
Mix in spices.
Flatten hash and make 4 shallow dents.
Add 1 egg and 3/4 tablespoon catsup to each shallow dent.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix with jello.
Add oil, water and eggs; heat 2 or 3 minutes.
Drain frozen berries and keep juice for icing.
Add berries and beat.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: quinoa with tofu
directions: Cut tofu into small cubes and marinate in teriyaki sauce for at least 1/2 hour.
Rinse Quinoa several times by running fresh water over it in a pot and pouring through a strainer.
In a saucepan, bring 2 cups water to a boil.
Add Quinoa, reduce heat, cover and simmer until all water is absorbed, about 15 to 20 minutes; set aside.
Heat oil in a large, nonstick skillet.
Add ginger and stir.
Add the onion and celery and cook until lightly browned.
Add cooked Quinoa, soy sauce and marinated tofu.
Stir once, cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Cook for 2 minutes, covered, or until vegetables are heated through.
Do not overcook.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: easy apricot jam
directions: In a large kettle combine apricots, orange juice and sugar. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix in lemon juice, cinnamon and ginger.
Remove from the heat and cool to room temperature.
Puree in a food processor or blender until smooth.
Spoon into jars or freezer containers, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Top with lids. Refrigerate or freeze.
Yields 4 cups.

title: meatless lasagna supreme
directions: Cook noodles.
Steam spinach leaves until soft.
Microwave zucchini for 2 minutes in 1/4 cup of water.
Put sliced water chestnuts on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 of Ricotta cheese and noodles.
Place the remainder of cheese on top of noodles.
Add onions and garlic.
Add zucchini and spinach.
Spread sauce over vegetable layer.
Layer noodles, sauce and grated Mozzarella cheese.
Cook for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma bavin's apple cake
directions: Mix thoroughly oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix in order given.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch greased pan at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour or slightly more. Will make very thick batter.
Bakes crusty on top.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine artichoke hearts, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice and garlic powder; mix well.
Spread in ungreased 9-inch quiche or pie pan or a 1-quart shallow casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with crackers or vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: blueberry sicles(kids)
directions: Combine berries and yogurt in blender.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into 3 1/2 ounce paper drinking cups.
Partially freeze; insert wooden sticks.
Freeze firm to eat.
Tear off paper cup. Experiment with other flavors.

title: butter barbecue beef patties
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, crumbs, green pepper, milk, catsup, salt and pepper.
Divide into patties on aluminum foil squares. Top each patty with a slice of onion and 2 to 3 tablespoons Butter Barbecue Sauce.
Bring up sides of foil, fold tight.
Fold ends over and over up close to meat.
Grill 3 inches from coals on grill for 10 to 12 minutes.
Turn and grill 10 to 12 minutes more.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup and water in heavy pot.
Cook over medium heat to boiling without stirring.
Continue boiling until temperature reaches 310° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 tablespoon oil flavoring and several drops of food coloring, to get desired color.
Pour on greased cookie sheet. Score with knife as candy hardens, working from edges to center. Cool completely and break into pieces.
Coat with confectioners sugar.

title: jo's easy pot roast
directions: Line a 13 1/2 x 9 3/4-inch Pyrex dish or pan with foil long enough to be able to fold over the meat.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and make into balls and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday nut crescent cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Roll dough into crescent shapes.
Bake in a 325° oven on ungreased cookie sheets for approximately 15 minutes.
Don't let cookies brown!
Cool slightly and roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: gourmet apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, egg, vinegar and pineapple juice; cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Cool and combine with Cool Whip.
Fold in pineapple and marshmallows.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: roasted corn and bacon relish
directions: Boil corn 4 minutes.
Allow to cool to room temperature.

Over a medium heat, grill corn 2 to 3 minutes or until lightly browned. Brush on the maple syrup and continue to grill for an additional 2 to 3 minutes or until the syrup begins to caramelize (it will turn golden brown).
Remove the corn from the grill and cool. With a sharp knife, remove the kernels.
Saute the bacon until crisp.
Add onion and cook until onion is clear.
Add the corn. Cook 2 minutes more.
Remove the corn mixture from heat; add the sage and salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana-berry shakes
directions: In a blender combine 2 cups strawberries, half of the bananas, 1/2 cup juice, 1/2 cup yogurt and 4 ice cubes.
Puree until thick and smooth.
Repeat with the remaining 2 cups strawberries, bananas, 1/2 cup juice, 1/2 cup yogurt and 4 ice cubes.

title: southern american turkey piccadillo
directions: Spray a large nonstick skillet or electric frying pan with cooking spray.
Spread turkey in skillet and brown over medium heat.
Crumble and brown evenly.
Drain and discard fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Stir frequently.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter into 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
In small bowl, combine 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over batter.
Pour hot water over top; do not stir.

title: russian dressing
directions: Take a heaping tablespoon of mayonnaise (as much as you need for the salad).
Enough chili sauce to cover the mayonnaise, stir it thoroughly to make a nice shrimp color, squeeze lemon over the mixture, along with a few drops of worcestershire sauce, stir thoroughly.
Horseradish is optional, it is great if you like your dressing tangy.

title: carla's homemade lemonade
directions: Add all ingredients to a pitcher and stir.
Add slices of lemon, if desired.
Pour over ice.

title: crab quiche
directions: Line pan with pastry and trim excess around edge of pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set overnight in a covered dish in refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour.
Add flour, one cup at a time, blending thoroughly.
Pour into well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until well done in the center.
Makes two large loaves or 6 to 7 small loaves.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt chips and oleo.
Gradually add sugar and milk.
Cook 8 minutes after full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove and add vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream or cake.
Keeps a long time in refrigerator.
Real good.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on package, adding lemon pudding.
Pour into a greased or sprayed 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until cake is done.
While still warm, poke holes in cake with a fork.
Mix lemonade and powdered sugar.
Pour over baked cake with holes and put back into oven a few minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Make it ahead, then it all blends together.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread in 9-inch square baking dish.
In separate bowl, beat eggs and stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour over bread.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Line pan with wax paper and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: beef-broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix Cheez Whiz, soup and onion in saucepan; set aside.
Grease a large casserole pan.
Place broccoli in bottom of pan.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over the top of the broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with slices of cheese or spoons of Cheez Whiz.
Makes approximately 6 to 8 servings.

title: pheasant in red cabbage
directions: Salt and pepper pheasant inside and out.
Make small incisions all over; insert slivers of bacon.
Heat shortening until hot in a baking pan.
Add pheasant, turning to coat with oil.
Roast in oven at 400° for 15 minutes, basting from time to time.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix pie filling and Cool Whip; blend well. Add remaining ingredients; pour into oblong pan and chill.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add half of the chili powder and the Cheez Whiz; stir over low heat until Cheez Whiz is melted.
Stir in tomato. Combine remaining Cheez Whiz, eggs, flour, salt and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Spoon meat mixture over batter to within 1 inch of edges.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil yams until tender; drain and peel.
Moderately mash yams. Melt butter and add yams.
Gradually add remaining ingredients. Beat mixture at high speed until smooth.
Consistency should be that of batter, but not too thin.

title: appetizer(use as an appetizer or serve as a main dish with steak or
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash mushrooms; carefully remove stems. Place, button side down, in shallow baking dish; brush with oil. Combine crabmeat, egg, mayonnaise, onion and lemon juice to make filling.
Mix together melted butter and bread crumbs.
Stuff each mushroom with filling and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 8 x 8 pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Good with ham dinner.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until done.
Drain and add milk, cheese and soup (do not add water to soup).
Stir well and pour into a casserole pan.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: no cook coconut pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat pudding mix, milk and coconut flavoring on low speed until combined.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and coconut.
Pour into crust. Sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken breasts in wine sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lay chicken breasts in bottom of baking dish large enough to allow only a single layer.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dutch almond cookies
directions: Combine melted butter or margarine and sugars; add eggs and beat. Sift together flour, cinnamon and baking soda; add to first mixture and blend well. Mix in nuts. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes or until it can be patted into rolls. (Dough will be sticky.) Wrap rolls in waxed paper and store in refrigerator overnight or until ready to use. Cut into 1/4-inch slices; place onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes 100 cookies.

title: mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a slow boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Strain before serving.

title: green beans
directions: Pour vinegar and sugar over drained beans in pan.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Fry bacon in a skillet.
Sprinkle over beans.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 12-cup muffin tin with margarine.
Combine oat bran, brown sugar, walnuts, raisins, baking powder and salt.
Add skim milk, egg and egg
white, honey and oil.
Mix until ingredients are just moistened.
Fill muffin tin and bake for 15 minutes, or until golden brown and a cake tester comes out clean.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix squash and onions. Sprinkle with salt. Let sit for 1 hour; drain. Mix vinegar, sugar, celery and mustard seeds. Add peppers. Bring to a hard boil. Add squash and onions to mixture. Bring to a hard boil and cook for approximately 15 minutes. Fill jars and seal.

title: clam spaghetti
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Meantime, heat oil in large skillet.
Add onion and garlic; cook until soft.
Add reserved clam juice and wine to skillet; boil until reduced by half, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add clams, thyme, parsley, salt (if needed; canned clams may be sufficiently salty) and red pepper flakes, if desired.
Drain pasta; toss with clam sauce and serve immediately.

title: grand hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put 4 teaspoons of the mix into a cup. Add boiling water.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O, pineapple and cottage cheese. Fold into Cool Whip. Chill before serving.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Saute onion
in
margarine
until clear color, add okra and cook
about
done.
Add chili powder, sugar, salt and chopped tomatoes.
Cook
until well done, stirring very often. Serves 4 to 6.

title: raisins pie
directions: Cook raisins in water until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix sugar and flour; add to raisins, butter and vanilla.
Mix the soda with buttermilk, then add to other mixture.
Mix well, pour into unbaked pie shell and stripe top with crust.
Bake at 350° until crust is browned as desired.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into one half inch slices.
Place a layer in bottom of buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and salt; dot with butter.
Continue layers until all ingredients are used, ending with sugar and butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 30 minutes or until glazed.
Add marshmallows the last 5 minutes to melt.
Brown lightly.
Serves 6.

title: grannys corn dish
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter. Mix eggs, corn (leave juice) and muffin mix in a large bowl. Pour into greased casserole. Put saute on top. Spoon sour cream on top. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: kung pao chicken
directions: Mix and set aside first 4 ingredients.
Heat stick-free skillet until very hot.
Add oil and chicken and stir-fry until done.
Remove chicken.
Add sauce ingredients and stir until combined and thick.
Return chicken to pan and add peanuts.
Heat and serve with rice.
(I like onions and green peppers in this, too!)

title: chili
directions: Fry ground beef in a 3-quart Dutch oven or 5 minutes in the microwave over a colander and bowl, stirring occasionally.
Mix all of the remaining ingredients with the ground beef and bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: easy sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix sweet potatoes with sugar; blend in 1 1/2 cups Bisquick. Stir in milk.
Put 1/2 cup Bisquick on board.
Dump mixture. Knead; cut out biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, taco seasoning and lemon juice in a mixing bowl (use electric mixer).
Lay out on a cookie sheet; cover with lettuce, tomatoes and shredded cheese.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Take nacho chips and use the taco salad like dip.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together flour, soda, eggs, sugar, salt and fruit cocktail. Pour batter into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool.
To serve, top with whipped cream.

title: chili
directions: Add chili powder to browned ground beef.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: ham 'n' tater bake
directions: Note:
Reduced-fat or fat-free mayonnaise may not be substituted for regular mayonnaise

title: super sloppy joes
directions: Chop onion fine.
In a large frying pan, brown meat with onion, salt and pepper; drain off grease.
Add ketchup and relish. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Place buns open on cookie sheet; spoon mixture on bottom half of bun.
Place 1/2 slice of cheese over each.
Put in hot oven or under broiler for a few minutes to toast bun and melt cheese.
Makes 10 small sandwiches. Great with French fries.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet, drain off fat.
Stir in other ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spinach salad with raspberry cream dressing
directions: Remove stems from spinach.
Wash and pat dry.
Tear into bite-sized pieces.
Combine spinach and other ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill.
Serve with Raspberry Cream Dressing (recipe follows).
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken monterey
directions: Butterfly chicken breasts.
Combine butter, oregano, basil and parsley in small bowl; set aside.
Stir together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.
Spread herb butter mix over chicken.
Cut Monterey Jack cheese in strips and roll them inside chicken breasts.
Dip chicken rolls in melted butter and roll in bread crumb mix.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: split pea and lentil soup
directions: Rinse and drain peas and lentils.
In a Dutch oven, combine peas, lentils, broth, carrots, celery, red pepper, onion, bay leaf and cumin.
Bring mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour or until peas are tender.
Remove bay leaf.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken for 20 minutes in water seasoned with salt and pepper to taste.
Take half of water used in boiling the chicken to cook broccoli until tender.
Combine soup and mayonnaise well; set aside.
(Add a little water if too dry.)
Spread prepared rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch, lightly greased pan.
Arrange broccoli on top of rice.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Pour soup and mayonnaise mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese liberally over casserole and sprinkle paprika for accent.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes (uncovered).

title: crisp sweet pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and garlic cloves in a large pan; add salt. Cover with crushed ice and mix thoroughly; let stand for 3 hours. Drain thoroughly. Combine sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar in large kettle. Bring just to a boil. Add cucumbers and onions. Bring just to a boil; heat through. Seal in hot, sterilized jars.

title: milk shakes
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients.
Cover; blend 30 to 60 seconds or until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: grandma jessie's sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into ball (walnut size).
Put on cookie sheet.
Dip wet fork into sugar and flatten.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Best when marinated overnight.

title: yellow cake with chocolate frosting
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bev's chocolate eclair torte
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with whole graham crackers. Mix pudding with milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Blend in whipped topping.
Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Place a second layer of crackers.
Pour remaining pudding mix over second layer.
Add third layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, egg and pecans by hand.
Press mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs with a mixer.
Mix until thin and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: nanny's salad
directions: Stir jello into pineapple.
Add fruit cocktail.
Stir in Cool Whip until well blended.
Chill or freeze.

title: ham jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in heavy kettle; add green pepper, onion and garlic. Cook until tender, but not browned.
Add Worcestershire sauce, thyme, water and tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Add rice and ham. Cover tightly and cook 25 minutes, until rice is tender.
Add mushrooms and shrimp; stir lightly and cook 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: black walnut macaroons
directions: *May substitute mini chocolate chips or chopped pecans or hickory nuts.

title: california coffee cake
directions: Mix and take out 1/2 cup for topping.
Add 1 egg to mixture. Add 1 cup buttermilk mixed with 1 teaspoon baking soda (batter will be thin).

title: pear relish
directions: Grind up pears, onions and pepper in meat chopper. Add other ingredients. Cook for 30 minutes after it begins to boil.

title: elvis presley potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until halfway cooked.
Peel and cube.
Put potatoes in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer onions, green pepper and cheese.
Butter both sides of bread, cube and put on top of cheese.
Melt butter and pour evenly over top. Bake at 375° until potatoes are done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: italian hamburger minestrone soup
directions: Saute onions and hamburger in oil until brown in a large kettle.
Add tomatoes, cabbage, potatoes, carrots, celery and green pepper.
Bring to a boil and add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve sprinkled with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: spanish rice
directions: Place oil and rice in skillet.
On low to medium heat, saute until golden brown (continue stirring).
Add onions; saute for 2 minutes.
Add water, tomato sauce and all spices.
Bring to a boil, reduce to simmer and cover tightly.
Cook approximately 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: italian cream cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.

Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well. Sift flour. Measure and sift again with the baking soda. Add flour alternately with buttermilk to the creamed mixture. Stir in vanilla, then coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter into three 8-inch or two 9-inch greased and floured round cake pans.
(Cake pans can be lined with greased and floured waxed paper.)
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pans about 5 minutes, then turn out on racks.
When cake is cool, frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Crush candy bars; set aside.
Pinch half of cake into small pieces.
Put in bowl.
In separate bowl, mix pudding according to directions.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half of candy bar mixture onto cake, then spread half of pudding mixture.
Repeat process to make 2 layers.
Keep refrigerated.
Make 5 or 6 hours before serving.

title: green rice
directions: Mix cheese with hot rice.
Add other ingredients in order named.
Bake in oiled casserole at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: granny smith's blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add the eggs and mix together.
Sift together dry ingredients and add milk and vanilla.
Mix and beat well.
Dust blueberries with flour and fold into batter.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: picante chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet.
Add chicken and garlic; cook and stir until chicken is almost cooked through, 5 minutes.
Drain and coarsely chop tomatoes, reserving juice.
Combine tomatoes, picante sauce, juice, pepper, onion and cumin, mixing well.
Stir into skillet.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and stir into skillet.
Simmer 1 minute until sauce is thickened, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice with cilantro and additional picante sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix Cool Whip and condensed milk together.
Add chocolate milk.
Freeze according to ice cream freezer manufacturers instructions.

title: mexican dip
directions: Put tomatoes, black olives and green chiles in bowl.
Mix vinegar, salt, oil and pepper.
Pour over tomato mixture.
Don't refrigerate more than 3 hours.
Serve with plain Doritos or tortilla chips.

title: salad dressing(for macaroni or potato salad)
directions: Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
When cool, add 1 cup salad dressing.
This can be cooked ahead of time, but don't add salad dressing until ready to use.
Can be kept for 2 weeks if refrigerated.

title: pork chop, potato, peas skillet dinner
directions: Fry pork chops in large skillet with a little oleo and oil. Pour undrained can of English peas over chops and add soy sauce (to taste).
Heat until contents of skillet are hot (do not bring to a boil).
Spoon peas and liquid over the creamed potatoes.

title: my favorite salad
directions: Mix the jellos in water and let set aside to cool. When syrupy, add the cottage cheese, mayonnaise, milk, celery, pecans and pineapple. Mix as you add each ingredients.
After all is mixed well, pour into a 13 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan and refrigerate.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Toss biscuit crumbs in melted oleo and set aside.
Add onion, tomato soup and the crumbled bacon to lima beans; mix well.
Put in a greased baking dish; top with biscuit mixture.
Bake, until done, at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine onions, carrots, celery and pepper in chicken broth. Boil until vegetables are tender.
Add potatoes and whipping cream.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Melt butter and stir the flour into butter.
Add this mixture to soup slowly.
Add can of celery soup.
Simmer.

title: sesame sticks
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
in
a bowl.
Let sit 10 minutes. Divide into
2 parts.
Roll on sprayed cookie sheet.
Cut into 4 x 1/3-inch sticks.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Makes 100 sticks.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut boneless chicken into bite-size pieces; boil only until done.
Do not overcook.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute pork over medium-high heat until pork is done, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine remaining syrup, vinegar, rice and Worcestershire sauce in a 2-cup liquid measure.
Add almonds and pineapple juice and then the pork mixture.
Simmer until rice is tender.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter and set aside.
In a 2-quart pot, put milk, parsley, salt, grated cheese and flour.
Add the onion and garlic mixture.
Turn stove top to medium heat and stir mixture until it becomes thick (like pudding).
Put sliced potatoes in a 12-inch baking pan.
Pour mixture over potatoes and cover.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Change oven temperature to 400°, uncover and bake 10 more minutes or until lightly brown.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut the toast into small squares (or substitute croutons).
In casserole dish, repeat layers of tomatoes and toast.
Sprinkle on salt and onion.
Pour melted butter or margarine over top.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: sausage and potato skillet
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add sausage, onions, hash browns, peppers, black pepper and garlic.
Saute over medium heat, 7 to 11 minutes.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or iron skillet.
Spread mushroom soup over vegetable mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven.
Spread fried onions and parsley and bake 2 minutes.

title: venison meat loaf(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Mix well.
Form into loaf on roasting pan.
Crisscross bacon strips on top of loaf, in an X design.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour until desired doneness.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Drain both cans of peaches, reserving 2/3 cup syrup.
Dice contents of one can; reserve 1 can for garnish on top of pie. Heat reserved syrup to boiling.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Place yogurt in bowl and slowly add hot Jell-O mixture while stirring yogurt.
Chill until almost set.
Fold in whipped topping and diced peaches.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set.

title: whacky cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Add vanilla, vinegar and butter.
Beat well.
Slowly stir in water and beat well.
Pour batter into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until done.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: mystery pie
directions: Add baking powder and nuts to crackers. Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Add to cracker mixture.
Put in buttered pie pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Let set 8 to 12 hours. Top with Cool Whip.

title: charoset
directions: This chopped apple mixture meaning "sweet like freedom" represents the mortar used by the Jews to build the pyramids for the Pharaohs.

title: grape nut pudding
directions: Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Heat oil; saute onion.
Add water and bouillon; bring to a boil.
Add noodles, salt and garlic powder; cook 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook 4 more minutes.
Add torn up cheese and stir until melted.
Add milk and heat.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Measure dry ingredients into a bowl.
Blend eggs, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Turn mixture into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan, then remove and cool completely on a rack.
(Really good toasted for breakfast!)

title: homemade noodles
directions: Measure flour into bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add egg yolks and whole egg.
With hands, mix eggs into flour.
Add water, mixing thoroughly.
Turn dough onto a well-floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Roll one part at a time paper thin, keeping remaining dough covered.
Roll up and cut into thin strips.
Let dry on tea towels for 24 hours.
Cook in chicken broth until tender, about 25 minutes.

title: jonita's favorite sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients and roll in 1-inch balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet about 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except broth, together in frying pan. Saute until wild rice looks slightly yellow. Add bouillon broth. Put everything in greased 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mallow dip for fruit
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Serve with sliced apples, strawberries, peaches, grapes, etc.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Stir together mashed bananas and bran cereal.
Let stand for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs and shortening.
Beat well. Stir in nuts.
Add flour mixture, stirring until it is moistened. Put in muffin pans.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Yields 20 to 24.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Place margarine in 1-quart casserole.
Microwave at High (100%) until melted, 30 seconds to 1 minute.
Stir in flour and salt. Blend in milk.
Microwave at High (100%) until thickened, 3 to 6 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking.

title: fresh shrimp salad
directions: Clean and devein 1 pound fresh shrimp.
Cook shrimp in one quart lightly salted water with 1/4 cup vinegar.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Let shrimp cool in cooking liquid until cold.
Remove shrimp and drain.
Place chunks of fresh crisp lettuce on salad plate and arrange tomato wedges on top.
Top each salad plate with shrimp and top with shredded horseradish.
Serves 4.

title: almond delight
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Pour melted margarine
over this and mix.
Bake this crumb mixture at 325° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir occasionally during baking period.

title: greek style rigatoni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in salad bowl; mix well.

title: spinach strata
directions: Cook spinach according to directions and drain well.
In buttered 2-quart shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inches) arrange half of bread cubes.
Spread spinach on bread evenly.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Top with remainder of bread and cheese.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: pupi pasta
directions: Chop tomatoes and basil.
Squeeze 3 to 5 cloves of garlic. Bring water to boil and cook pasta.
When done, drain and quickly mix with vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve while very hot, accompanied with fresh Parmesan cheese to grate on top.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie(one 9-inch pie)
directions: Beat the cream cheese at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Add sugar and peanut butter, beating well. Gradually add milk, beating until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and spoon into crust.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Freeze.

title: perfect pie crust(makes 5 crusts)
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Add shortening and mix until crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat together the water, vinegar and egg.
Combine the 2 mixtures until all ingredients are moistened; mix well.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in pan; add onion.
Cook.
Remove from heat.
Mix Jiffy mix, eggs, sour cream and broccoli; add onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: super-duper chocolate cookies
directions: Chill dough several hours.
It can be placed in freezer for shorter time.
Form into small balls, and roll in powdered sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: frankfurters with hamburger sauce
directions: Brown onions in fat, add hamburger and cook for few minutes, tossing with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer gently for 45 minutes.
Prepare frankfurters to suit individual taste, either boil, steam or broil.
Split long rolls, place franks in center and fill center cavity with hamburger sauce.
Serve very hot.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake rolls (spread out) on cookie sheet as directed.
Mix other ingredients and spread over cool crust.
Add vegetables and cheese.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

Sprinkle onion and cheese over crust. Blend together all remaining ingredients, adding spinach last. Pour over cheese and onions. Bake at 450° on the bottom rack for 15 minutes. REDUCE heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer. Remove from oven and let cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry-banana shake
directions: Put milk and banana in blender container. Add ice cream. Blend smooth. Serves 2 to 3.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: spicy dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in crock-pot and allow to simmer.

title: light and moist cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325°.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, bake approximately 30 minutes.
In an 8 x 3-inch pan, bake approximately 50 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients in crock pot and heat till cheese is melted.
Stir.
Dip with Doritos or tortilla chips.

title: harvest salad
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: roast pork
directions: Place pork, fat side up.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Rub over surface of meat.
Roast at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Combine orange peel, juice and brown sugar; spoon over roast.
Return to oven and roast 1 hour longer, basting frequently.
Make gravy. Add flour, dry mustard, marjoram and water.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: meat loaf (deer)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients well.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holly leaves
directions: Slowly melt marshmallows with oleo.
Stir in food coloring, then gently stir in corn flakes until coated.
Drop on waxed paper and decorate with red hots (cinnamon candies).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and syrup together.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook to a soft ball stage (about 8 minutes).
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla, nuts and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour onto a buttered platter until hard.
Cut into pieces.

title: fast and easy lasagna
directions: Boil egg noodles according to package directions.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cook noodles according to directions; drain and mix with chicken. Melt butter; saute celery, onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with flour, gradually stir in broth until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper; stir in cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly; stir in olives and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken and noodles.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Can be prepared ahead and refrigerated. Allow 15 more minutes for cooking.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Blend flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream shortening and vanilla together.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Mixing until well blended after each addition, alternately add dry ingredients in fourths and a mixture of the evaporated milk and lemon juice in thirds to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry, peaks are formed.
Fold into the batter.

title: chicken divan over rice
directions: Parboil chicken breasts 20 to 25 minutes.
Parboil broccoli 5 to 8 minutes until tender.
Mix soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise together.

title: stroganoff sandwiches
directions: In skillet, cook meat and onion until meat is browned; drain. Stir in sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and 3/4 teaspoon salt. Heat through; do not boil.

title: mexi-beef bites
directions: Cook and stir beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat until beef is no longer pink.
Pour off drippings.
Stir in cheeses, chilies, taco sauce and eggs.
Transfer mixture to 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean and top is golden brown. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Cut into 36 squares.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: coffee cake #2
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, water, oil, extract and vanilla. Add 4 eggs, beat in one at a time.
Put 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13 pan. Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Put 1/2 of this over cake mix. Spread the rest of cake mix, then rest of topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl. Mix together. Work with hands. Pour into greased and floured bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let cool in pan before removing.

title: swiss dill sauce
directions: Cook and stir cheese and mayo over low heat until cheese melts.
Beat smooth with rotary beater.
Stir in sour cream and dill.
Serve over cauliflower, asparagus, broccoli or carrots. Makes 1 cup.

title: cornbread sage dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Place in greased 3 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Put Blue cheese, buttermilk, onion and garlic in blender and blend.
Add mayonnaise.

title: zesty lemon-glazed steaks
directions: In a small bowl, combine steak sauce, lemon peel, garlic, pepper and oregano. Brush on both sides of steaks.
Grill steaks over medium heat or broil 6 inches from heat source for 5 minutes on each side or to desired doneness, brushing with sauce occasionally.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut icebox cake
directions: Bake according to directions.
When it is cool, slice into 4 sections horizontally.
(Each layer must be sliced once.)

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Knead ingredients. Chill thoroughly. Roll into small balls. Freeze until solid. To finish, melt 1 pound bitter chocolate in top of double boiler. (For 4 batches, use 1 1/2 pounds chocolate.) Add a few shavings of paraffin. Drop frozen balls into chocolate. Lift out with fork. Shake off excess chocolate. Slide onto wax paper. Cool and pack.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut oleo into dry cake mix until crumbly. Mix in coconut. Pat mixture lightly into 13 x 9-inch pan, building up slight edges.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange peach slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on peaches.
Blend sour cream and egg; drizzle over peaches.
(Topping will not completely cover peaches.)
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown. (Do not overbake.)
Serve warm.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a medium boiler mix flour, sugar and salt with the chocolate syrup; add egg yolks and stir well; add the milk and stir until everything is blended smoothly.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter and stir.
Pour into baked pie crust. Use egg whites for topping.

title: maply appetizers
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Cut sausages in thirds, crosswise and brown in skillet.

title: mexican pasta shells
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce.
Add to ground beef.
Add green chilies, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup French fried onions.
Stuff shells with ground beef mixture.

title: andover kielbasa
directions: Slice kielbasa about 1/2-inch thick.
Simmer in chili sauce, bourbon and brown sugar mixture for 2 hours.
May be made ahead and reheated.
Serve as an appetizer.

title: chicken 'n peaches salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions, but omit fat. Cool in mixing bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise, green pepper, green onion and tarragon.
Add chicken; toss lightly to coat.
Cover and chill.
Shortly before serving, add peaches and toss.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole and rice
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Saute onion in butter.
Add frozen broccoli and cook in butter, adding no water.
Add jar of Cheez Whiz to cooked broccoli and stir until melted.
Blend in cream of chicken soup and mushrooms.
Add rice to mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
May be prepared ahead of time and frozen.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup(preparation time: 10 minutes; simmering time: 50 minutes.)
directions: In a Dutch oven or large saucepan, cover chicken with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes or until tender. Reserve broth. Bone and shred chicken, then set aside. Saut celery, onion and carrots in butter until soft. Add flour. Cook while constantly stirring until golden brown. Add broth, salt and pepper and bring to boil. Add noodles. Cook until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally. Add reserved shredded chicken and half and half.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Brown meat with garlic powder, oregano, basil and onion. Drain well.
Pour sauce into large pan and mix with meat.
Heat well.
Cook noodles in water and olive oil.
Combine cottage cheese with 2 beaten eggs.
Mix well with other cheeses, saving 1 cup of Parmesan for top layer.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 6 to 8 hours or overnight before serving.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Butter a 9-inch pie pan.
Cover the bottom with cranberries. Sprinkle nuts and brown sugar. Beat egg in small mixing bowl. Add flour and sugar. Pour in melted butter.
Mix well and pour over top of cranberries.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool. Top with whipped cream.

title: souped up chicken
directions: Dust in flour, salt and pepper the chicken.
Brown well in margarine or oil.
Lay onion on top of chicken.
Add soup and water, poultry seasoning and salt and pepper to season.
Cover tightly and cook over very low heat for 45 minutes.
One cup milk or 1 cup dairy sour cream may be added just before serving, if desired.

title: hot dog hors d'oeuvres(hot)
directions: Cut hot dogs bite size.
Place in crock-pot.
Add beer over; add Tabasco sauce.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
If not hot enough, add rest of the Tabasco.
Serve with chili sauce dip.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in large brown grocery bag.
Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt in 2-quart microwave bowl.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Bring to boil. Microwave 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour mixture over popped corn and peanuts in bag.
Close bag and shake well. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake bag and microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into large roaster and let cool.
Separate. Store in tightly covered container.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order given in mixer on high speed. Pour into 10-inch greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This pies makes its own crust, filling and topping, while baking.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream oleo, cream cheese, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add egg and milk.
Beat well; add flour.
Stir in coconut.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top with one-half maraschino cherry. Bake at 325° for 16 to 20 minutes.
Do not let brown.

title: hot chocolate supreme
directions: Combine both ingredients in medium saucepan and stir over low heat until hot and smooth.
Serve immediately, garnishing, if desired, with a dollop of whipped topping.
Sprinkle with frozen Milky Way bar.
Makes 2 or 3 servings.

title: chicken with pear-cream sauce
directions: Pour chicken stock into saucepan and bring to a simmer.
Peel pears, save parings and cut pears into uniform pieces.
Add to chicken stock and cook until tender (5 to 10 minutes).
Drain pears and reserve stock.
Puree pears in blender or food processor.

title: robbins pie
directions: Mix together flour, melted margarine and 1/2 cup sugar. Press into pan. Cook at 400° for 20 minutes. Cool completely.

title: macaroni soup
directions: Put shoulder bone in 5 or 6-quart pot (with some meat on it). Cover with water.
Cut up onions.
Add to pot.
Simmer for 90 minutes.
Remove bone from pot.
Add cut-up tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Add elbow macaroni.
Boil 14 minutes.
Add cut-up pieces of smoked shoulder.

title: hot dog bites
directions: You will also need toothpicks and a crock-pot.

title: cabbage beef casserole(an alternative to the usual cabbage rolls)
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef in oil until browned, drain off fat. Stir in onion, garlic, salt and pepper, tomato sauce and water. Bring to boil, stir in rice. Simmer, covered about 20 minutes. Place half the cabbage in buttered baking dish. Cover with half the rice mixture. Repeat layers. Bake covered at 350° for one hour.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place one layer of potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle a thin layer of garlic salt on the potatoes.
Slice oleo thin and place 1/3 on this layer.
Repeat until ingredients are used.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with blender until well mixed.
Crush Oreo cookies with blender.
Layer cookies, mix, pudding and cookies.
Top with gummy worms; refrigerate.

title: california vegetable casserole
directions: Put vegetables into casserole dish.
Add shredded cheese. Combine crushed crackers with margarine and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: carrot nut cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; set aside.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs, beating after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mixing well.
Blend in grated carrots, undrained pineapple, chopped nuts and raisins.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 55 minutes or until done by test.
Cool and frost.

title: noodles
directions: Mix in bowl.
Add a little water, if needed, and make dough ball until smooth and not too stiff.
Roll out on floured board and roll into large, thin circle.
Cut into strips (thin or wide). Drop in kettle with meat ball and cook until done.

title: cake donuts
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Beat eggs until light.
Add to oil and sugar the lemon flavoring.
Beat well.
Add sifted flour, alternately with milk, beating well after each addition, with electric mixer.
Cover bowl and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: turkey ham sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 cups or enough filling for 10 sandwiches.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Drain, wash and mash pinto beans in bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients into beans in order.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 (9-inch) pies.

title: cobb salad
directions: Chop items very fine.
Toss all together with Good Seasons Italian dressing.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the meat and add all other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with Fritos, cornbread or whatever.

title: cheesy pigs in a blanket
directions: Will also need toothpicks.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine stuffing mix and butter or margarine.
Mix until blended. Spread some in the bottom of a lightly greased shallow baking pan.
Cover with a layer of chicken.
Set aside.
Combine broth and soups in a saucepan.
Mix well.
Cook five minutes or until heated.
Spoon some evenly over chicken in baking dish.
Repeat layers of stuffing and chicken until all are used, ending with stuffing.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Place in a large mixing bowl; with electric or hand beater, blend well.
Pour into a punch bowl and gently stir in a quart of chilled ginger ale.

title: cheese strata
directions: Place 6 slices of bread, buttered side down in buttered casserole.
Spread meat over bread, cheese over meat.
Cover with 6 bread slices, buttered side up. Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over all and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, 1/2 powdered sugar and chocolate kisses together in a large pan. Add cereal to mixture. Stir to coat. Place mixture in a large paper bag. Add last of powdered sugar and shake until all coated. Bag in Ziploc bags.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix all
the ingredients together and bake at 350°
for 1 hour in 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix 1 cup hot water with Jell-O until dissolved.
Mix in cup of cold water.
Put in refrigerator until semi hardened.
Drain pineapple and add to Jell-O.
Mix in cranberry, walnuts and celery.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: great-grandmother shrout's sand tarts
directions: Combine butter/Crisco, eggs and brown sugar.
Gradually add flour.
Mix well.
Put in icebox in mixing bowl and cover with waxed paper and cloth to chill.
Remove from icebox and take by small amounts and roll very thin.
Cut in circles with cookie cutter.
Put on cookie sheet and apply smear mixture with pastry brush.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Dot with a nut in center.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.
Time will vary from oven to oven.

title: rhubarb meringue pie
directions: Cut rhubarb and pour boiling water over and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and put in double boiler.
Add 2 eggs, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Cook until thickens; pour in baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue.
Bake in slow oven (325°) until meringue is browned, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple salad with blanched almonds
directions: Make a custard by boiling milk and adding eggs, sugar, flour and vinegar. Cool.	Add crushed pineapple, almonds, marshmallows and whipped cream. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Keep 3/4 cup hot water from broccoli.
Salt the water and combine with flour.
Stir until smooth; mix with broccoli.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in cream of chicken soup, 1 soup can milk and cheese.
Pepper to taste.
Stir occasionally.
May burn easily.

title: maine blueberry cakes(or "mary lou's blues")
directions: Mix together all ingredients to a workable dough, adding flour only if needed.
Roll out dough and cut with a round cookie cutter.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Delicious.

title: squash dressing
directions: Boil squash and mash.
Bake cornbread.
Mix together.
Add soup and broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; place in casserole dish. Cook stuffing mix, also according to directions on package.
Cook butter, flour, milk and mushroom soup together.
Pour over broccoli and stuffing mix in the casserole dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese on top.
May use bread crumbs on top, also.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Butter the bottom and sides of a large baking dish.
In a large bowl, combine chicken pieces and prepared stuffing.
Mix well.

title: creamy carrot soup
directions: This elegant soup uses no cream.
Potatoes are the thickening secret.

title: jo's quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix the yeast and the warm water, then add 1 tablespoon of the sugar; set aside.
Mix the remaining sugar, oil, salt and egg. Slowly add the 2 mixtures together.
When thoroughly mixed, start adding the flour to make a smooth batter; will be thick.
Put batter into buttered bowl.
Start adding the flour to make a smooth batter; will be thick.
Put batter into buttered bowl; cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
Dough will keep in the refrigerator up to 5 days.

When ready to use, roll out on a well-floured surface to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick; thickness depends on how you choose to bake rolls. Roll to 1/4-inch thickness, cut small rounds and place 2 rounds, standing on end in well-greased muffin tins.
This makes a fan roll.
You can roll 1/2-inch thick, cut a little larger rounds and place in well-greased pan.
These make pull apart rolls. Cover the rolls with a kitchen towel and put them in a warm place to rise for about 2 hours.
Bake in a 375° oven until golden brown, about 15 minutes. You have to watch them and not over- or underbake.
Makes about 2 dozen rolls.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, stir together remaining ingredients.
Drop mixture by spoonful over the sauce in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until light brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Clean shrimp and boil.
Add salt and pepper to season.
Cook macaroni.
Chop bell pepper, celery, onion and eggs.
Mix chopped shrimp, macaroni, eggs, celery, bell pepper, onion, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together in pan.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Put pecans in.
Break biscuits in 4. Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Put in pan.
Melt butter.
Add 1 cup brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: spanish bars
directions: Make sure mixture is very cool before adding to dry ing.

title: chicken waikiki beach
directions: Coat chicken with flour. Brown in oil. Place in baking dish. Add salt and pepper. Drain pineapple, reserving syrup. Add water to make 1 1/4 cups.

title: barbecued baby ribs
directions: Place ribs in large Dutch oven.
Combine water, vinegar, sugar, salt, spices and garlic; pour over ribs.
Cover tightly. Cook slow for 1 1/4 hours.
Refrigerate overnight.
Combine catsup, jelly and 1/2 cup marinade in small saucepan and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Place ribs on grill; brush with glaze. Broil each side until brown and heated through.
Serves 6.

title: judy's dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off excess fat.
Mix chili and Velveeta; stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Add a few drops of hot sauce or hot picante sauce.
Serve with Fritos.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook box of rice according to directions and set aside.
Cook sausage and drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients including the rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 2-quart casserole dish. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple pistachio salad
directions: Blend softened Cool Whip with pudding.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture along with marshmallows and pecans.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: impossible apple pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Mix apples and spices.
Turn into pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients except streusel until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Sprinkle with streusel.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Measure water into mixing bowl.
Add yeast, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Mix in flour. Do not knead.
Place greased side up in greased mixing bowl. Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally as it rises.

title: ham-salami-cheese roll-up
directions: In lightly greased jelly roll pan roll out bread dough to edge of pan.
Layer ham, salami, then cheese.
Sprinkle seasoning. Begin to roll from the lower edge.
Seal the ends and other side. Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water over direct heat for 5 minutes.
While hot, add cheese, beaten eggs, margarine and salts.
Put in 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Wash shrimp.
Combine 2 onions, vinegar and water; heat to boiling.
Add shrimp and boil 15 to 20 minutes or until pink. Remove shrimp; shell and clean.
Save the stock.
Chop remaining onion and brown in butter, then blend in flour and add okra.
Add strained stock slowly, stirring constantly.
Add rice, tomatoes, seasonings and shrimp.
Simmer until okra and tomatoes are cooked. Remove the bay leaves.
This will generously serve 8.

title: schnitzles(hamburgers)
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Heat skillet with 1 tablespoon oil and make medium sized patties out of meat mixture. Brown broth sides in skillet over medium-low heat.

title: deviled pork chops
directions: Place chops in baking dish.
Blend tomatoes and other ingredients.
Pour sauce over chops.
At this point, can be frozen up to 1 month.
Thaw 3 to 4 hours.
Cover and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt bars and 1/2 cup butter in pan over low heat.
Cool. Cream remaining butter and sugar until creamy and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and buttermilk.
Stir until smooth.
Add cool melted candy bars.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg; mix and add tomato soup.
Add flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and baking soda. Mix and add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° one hour.

title: oat bran muffins(good for those watching cholesterol levels)
directions: Chop
apples
and
nuts.
Mix dry ingredients with raisins, apples,
carrots
and nuts.
Stir in moist ingredients. Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: apple tart
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Fill shell with apple halves, cut side down.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over apples; sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter. Fill pie shell with milk and bake at 410° for 10 minutes, then at 375° until apples are soft and brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cheese, onion, soup, mayonnaise and eggs well and add broccoli.
Pour into baking dish.
Brown cornbread stuffing in melted butter and spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: apple chip cake
directions: In large bowl, beat oil, sugar and eggs, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: torii rice
directions: *Make from 6 bouillon cubes melted in 2 cups hot water or 2 cups chicken stock if you have it.

title: roast and gravy
directions: Place meat in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Combine soup mix, mushroom soup and water.
Pour mixture over meat and cover securely with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: dairy delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix pecans, flour and butter; pat out into baking dish (8 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: coconut pudding cake
directions: Mix well. Can be mixed in blender.
Bake in a greased aluminum Jell-O mold ring or Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour or so at 350°.
Cool well before turning out of pan.

title: pumpkin lattice pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 375° F. Let pie crusts stand at room temperature 15 minutes.
Lightly sprinkle large round stone with flour.
Gently unfold one pie crust onto center of baking stone. Lightly brush with water using a pastry brush.
Sprinkle 1/4 c. pecans over crust.
Unfold second crust and place over first crust, matching edges and pressing lightly to seal.
Roll crusts out together to the edge of baking stone.
Fold edges of crust 1/2 inch toward center, Forming an even border, press to seal seam.
Prick the entire crust with a fork.
Lightly beat egg and spread over crust.
Sprinkle sugar evenly over crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to cooling rack.
Cool 15 minutes. Carefully slide crust onto round platter; cool completely.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Set aside 1 can of soup.
Mix other ingredients well.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put remaining can of soup on top of loaf and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in
boiling,
salted
water until tender. Mash potatoes in large bowl
of electric mixer.	Add 1 package cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper to taste and crushed garlic clove; beat until
smooth
and
light.
Gently
stir in chopped chives.
Spoon into
lightly
buttered baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Dot	with butter or margarine and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until slightly golden in color.

title: stone soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until golden and tender.
Add ground beef and garlic clove and cook until meat is brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: carolina colonial pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar on medium speed of electric mixer until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Stir in pecans, raisins and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour filling into crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: stir and bake carrot cake
directions: About 4 hours before serving or early in the day, preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-cup fluted baking mold or 10-inch Bundt pan.
In a large bowl, with spoon, mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a small bowl, with fork, beat eggs slightly. Stir in salad oil and vanilla extract.

Stir egg mixture, 3 cups shredded carrots (reserve remaining 1/4 cup to garnish top), prunes and pecans into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. Spoon batter into pan. Bake 65 to 70 minutes until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove cake from pan; cool completely on rack.
When cake is cool, prepare Cream-Cheese Drizzle.
Spoon drizzle on top of cake; garnish with reserved shredded carrots.
Makes 16 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in cooked squash.
Mix stuffing mix with butter.
Spread 1/2 crumb mixture into bottom of casserole.
Pour squash mixture over, then top with remaining crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and season.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Note:
I double this recipe and bake in crock-pot.

title: swedish ham balls
directions: Make balls of the first 5 ingredients.
Mix the last 4 ingredients and pour over ham balls.
Put in baking dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: apple cake
directions: Add all together and bake at 375° until brown or done.

title: annie's chicken casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, layer chicken pieces and Swiss cheese. Mix soup, wine and water.
Pour over chicken in casserole. Sprinkle with crumbs and drizzle with butter.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour, uncovered for 1/2 hour.
Serve with corkscrew noodles.

title: zucchini supper
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
Peel and cube zucchini.
Add to the beef and simmer until tender.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Cover and serve when the cheese is melted.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat with mixer the flour, sugar and milk until batter is smooth.
Pour melted butter in a 3-quart casserole.
Pour batter over butter (do not stir).
Spoon peaches on top (do not stir).
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until brown.

title: scallop kabobs
directions: Thaw scallops or fish, if frozen. Drain pineapple chunks, reserving the juice for marinade. Set pineapple chunks aside.

title: cream puffs
directions: In same pot, boil water and add butter;
let
it
melt. Turn heat off.
Add 2 cups flour; mix with
fork.
Add
eggs, one at a time (mix well after each).
Spoon	onto cookie sheet (1 heaping teaspoonful).
Bake at 350° for 1
hour
(or
until light brown). Pastry will puff and double in size when done.

title: kfc cole slaw
directions: Blend sugar, salt, pepper, celery salt.
Add mayonnaise, milk, buttermilk, vinegar and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth. Pour over cabbage and carrots.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: cereal crunchies
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Start count with first bubble, cook 1 minute.
Stir in cereal; mix well.
Spread in large pan or shape into balls.
Cool.
Enjoy!

title: good baked beans casserole
directions: Brown onions, bacon and hamburger together. Add mustard, vinegar, brown sugar and catsup. Stir in undrained pork and beans, butter beans, green lima beans and kidney beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Do not dilute soup.
Cook and bone chicken and break into bits.
Combine the torn bread, 2 beaten eggs, chicken and both soups.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in 1-inch slices and fry.
Combine all ingredients. Bake in a greased casserole dish for 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.
Add bacon.
Serve.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn and set aside.
Mix all the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda, mixing well.
Pour over popped corn, coating well.
Put in shallow pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: sugar pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together in a medium mixing bowl. Add boiling water and butter. Mix with a whisk until smooth. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes and then at 350° until set (around 30 minutes).

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup butter. Mix. Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and spices. Beat well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine nuts, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle over pumpkin filling.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until filling is set.
Great served with whipped cream.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; saute celery.
Add soups, cheese, onions, seasoning as desired and broccoli.
Pour mixture over rice; bake 10 minutes at 350°.
This can be stretched by adding another package of broccoli.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat all ingredients in a pot until margarine is melted.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: taffy-apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In a large bowl, stir together pineapple chunks and marshmallows; cover and chill for up to 24 hours.

title: pickled slim mushroom *
directions: Rinse mushrooms, pat dry and cut in halves.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms and boil 2 minutes.
Spoon mushrooms into jars, pour liquid over mushrooms.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Crumble bacon over salad.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel 6 to 10 red potatoes.
Slice into thick slices.
Boil in lightly salted water until fork-tender.
Drain.
Layer potatoes in an ovenproof dish with teaspoon of soft margarine and pieces of Velveeta cheese.
Put in hot oven long enough to melt margarine and cheese.
Gently stir to thoroughly coat potatoes with melted margarine and cheese.

title: lime punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, water and sugar.
Mix well and then add juices.
Let stand in refrigerator until time to serve.
Just before serving add ginger ale and sherbet.
Drink and enjoy.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, soda and eggs.
Add fruit cocktail and chopped nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add chicken broth. Cook over medium heat until mixture is thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly. Stir in salt and pepper. Stir in chicken and next 3 ingredients. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.

title: date nut spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, honey, dates and walnuts until well mixed.
Serve with wheat crackers.
Also good on pumpkin bread. Yields 3 cups.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix onion with squash and cook for 5 minutes. Drain all but a small amount of the liquid. Add sour cream,

and chicken soup and mix well. Melt margarine and add dressing mix. Place half of dressing mix in bottom of deep pan, spreading evenly. Add squash mixture and top with remaining dressing. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Remove from pan.
Saute onions until golden.
Add water, bouillon, soup and caraway to pan with onions. Simmer until it starts to boil.
Reduce heat and add chops. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve with boiled noodles, red cabbage or green beans.
(Gravy tastes like rye bread.)

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix oil, dressing, dill weed and garlic salt.
Pour over crackers and stir until crackers are coated.
Lay on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir and bake 2 minutes.
Don't let them get too brown.
Bottom layer will brown quickly.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and water until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved. Cool.
Arrange peaches in pie crust; pour cooled filling over peaches.
Chill in refrigerator until set, at least 2 hours. Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: turtle cake(sin cake)
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on the box.
Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels, butter and milk; stir constantly and add chocolate, nuts and coconut.
